02:40.935 --> 02:45.438
BOYS [SINGING]:
Hark the herald angels sing

02:45.606 --> 02:49.859
Glory to the newborn king

02:50.027 --> 02:54.280
Peace on Earth and mercy mild

02:54.490 --> 02:58.201
God and sinners reconciled

02:58.410 --> 02:59.494
Joyful all the nations...

02:59.662 --> 03:02.413
There will be no peace on Earth
with all that blooming noise going on.

03:02.581 --> 03:05.083
- Here you are, boys.
BOYS [IN UNISON]: Thanks, guv'nor.

03:05.251 --> 03:06.417
BOY 1:
Come on.

03:06.585 --> 03:07.752
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

03:07.920 --> 03:10.463
BOY 2: All right, come on, hurry up.
BOY 3: All right, all right.

03:10.631 --> 03:12.548
BOY 1:
Come on, this house here.

03:14.176 --> 03:16.844
[SINGING]
Hark the herald angels sing

03:17.096 --> 03:21.391
Glory to the newborn king

03:21.558 --> 03:25.728
Peace on Earth and mercy mild

03:25.896 --> 03:27.522
God and sinners reconciled

03:30.401 --> 03:34.445
Joyful all ye nations rise

03:34.613 --> 03:38.825
Join the triumph of the skies

03:38.993 --> 03:42.245
With the angelic host proclaim

03:42.413 --> 03:43.496
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

03:43.664 --> 03:45.415
Christ is born in Bethlehem

03:45.582 --> 03:47.667
Infernal, horrible caterwauling.

03:47.835 --> 03:51.337
Hark the herald angels sing

03:51.505 --> 03:55.216
Glory to the newborn king

03:55.384 --> 03:58.886
Why can't they leave a man
in peace?

03:59.054 --> 04:00.346
Get on with your work, Cratchit.

04:00.514 --> 04:03.099
Hark the herald angels sing
Glory to...

04:03.267 --> 04:07.020
BOYS: Merry Christmas.
- Get away from me, you scavengers.

04:07.813 --> 04:09.314
Blimey. Who's he?

04:09.481 --> 04:10.648
That's Father Christmas.

04:10.858 --> 04:13.526
A plague on Father Christmas.

04:13.736 --> 04:16.487
And he sends his best
to you too, guv'nor.

04:16.654 --> 04:18.488
[BOYS LAUGHING]

04:20.117 --> 04:23.661
BOY 4: Regards, Father Christmas.
- Humbug.

04:24.121 --> 04:25.204
Insolent young ruffians.

04:25.372 --> 04:28.833
Coming here
with their Christmas nonsense.

04:31.879 --> 04:33.921
Beware, Cratchit.

04:34.340 --> 04:35.882
You have a dangerous
sense of humor.

04:36.050 --> 04:38.009
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

04:38.177 --> 04:40.595
Hell fire and damnation.

04:40.763 --> 04:43.473
Don't they know
that I'm trying to run a business here?

04:43.640 --> 04:47.060
Uncle Ebenezer,
I cannot tell you what a joy it is

04:47.269 --> 04:48.603
to see your happy, smiling face.

04:48.771 --> 04:51.731
- Hmm, it's you.
- A Merry Christmas, Uncle Ebenezer.

04:51.899 --> 04:52.982
God save you.

04:53.150 --> 04:56.110
God save me from Christmas.
It's a lot of humbug.

04:56.278 --> 04:59.364
Christmas a humbug? Come now,
I'm sure you don't mean that.

04:59.573 --> 05:01.741
And I'm sure that I do mean that.

05:01.909 --> 05:04.243
Merry Christmas indeed.

05:04.620 --> 05:07.163
What reason have you got
to be merry? You're poor enough.

05:07.331 --> 05:09.957
What reason have you got
to be miserable? You're rich enough.

05:10.125 --> 05:13.044
There is no such thing as rich enough.
Only poor enough.

05:13.212 --> 05:15.129
Don't be so dismal, Uncle Ebenezer.

05:15.297 --> 05:17.382
What else can I be
when I live in a world

05:17.549 --> 05:21.844
full of fools babbling Merry Christmas
at one another?

05:22.054 --> 05:24.347
What's Christmas
but a time for finding yourself

05:24.515 --> 05:27.225
a year older and not a day richer?

05:27.393 --> 05:29.894
There's nothing merry in that.

05:30.062 --> 05:31.729
If I could work my will, nephew,

05:31.897 --> 05:35.400
every idiot who goes about
with Merry Christmas on his lips

05:35.567 --> 05:38.319
should be boiled with his own pudding
and buried with a stake

05:38.487 --> 05:39.987
of holly through his heart.

05:40.197 --> 05:41.864
Oh, God forbid, uncle.

05:42.074 --> 05:45.326
You keep Christmas in your way
and let me keep it in mine.

05:45.494 --> 05:46.744
But you don't keep it.

05:46.912 --> 05:48.871
Then let me... Get off my ledger.

05:49.039 --> 05:51.457
You'll ruin my binding.

05:51.625 --> 05:54.001
Then let me leave it alone, sir.

05:54.169 --> 05:58.881
And be good enough to leave me alone
during business hours.

05:59.049 --> 06:02.009
Seven o'clock on Christmas eve?
That's not business hours.

06:02.177 --> 06:05.221
That's drudgery for the sake of it.
And an insult to all men of good will.

06:05.389 --> 06:08.724
- Hear, hear.
- Thank you, Bob Cratchit.

06:16.608 --> 06:18.484
Another word from you, Cratchit,

06:18.652 --> 06:22.613
and you will celebrate Christmas
by losing your position.

06:23.407 --> 06:24.740
Yes, sir.

06:24.908 --> 06:27.034
Sorry, Mr. Scrooge.

06:28.787 --> 06:30.246
You're quite a powerful speaker, sir.

06:30.414 --> 06:32.874
I wonder you don't go into politics.
You're fool enough.

06:33.041 --> 06:34.083
[CHUCKLES]

06:34.251 --> 06:35.418
Come now.

06:35.586 --> 06:36.961
Don't be angry.

06:37.129 --> 06:38.546
Dine with me wife and me tomorrow.

06:39.423 --> 06:41.591
As though
you hadn't got enough problems,

06:41.758 --> 06:43.176
you went and got yourself married.

06:43.343 --> 06:45.720
Now why in God's name
did you ever do that?

06:46.180 --> 06:47.638
Because I fell in love with the lady.

06:47.848 --> 06:49.182
If there's one thing in the world

06:49.349 --> 06:51.893
more nauseating
than a Merry Christmas,

06:52.060 --> 06:57.523
it's the hypocrisy of a happy marriage
with some idiot lovesick female.

06:57.691 --> 06:59.317
Good afternoon, sir.

06:59.526 --> 07:00.776
My offer stands.

07:00.944 --> 07:02.612
You are always welcome, uncle.

07:02.779 --> 07:04.071
Just like Christmas itself.

07:04.281 --> 07:05.740
I said good afternoon.

07:05.949 --> 07:07.366
Merry Christmas, uncle.

07:07.534 --> 07:09.327
You too, Bob Cratchit. And your family.

07:09.495 --> 07:12.413
Thank you, sir.
And to your good lady.

07:12.915 --> 07:15.500
Oh, and uncle, happy New Year.

07:15.709 --> 07:17.960
Good afternoon.

07:29.932 --> 07:32.058
[CLOCK CHIMING]

07:42.778 --> 07:46.739
Excuse me, sir.
But, well, it's 7:00, sir.

07:53.497 --> 07:55.289
Correct, Cratchit.

07:56.750 --> 07:59.001
Well, I don't wish to be impertinent,
Mr. Scrooge,

07:59.169 --> 08:03.965
but, uh, would it be too much trouble
for me to have my, uh, wages, sir?

08:05.634 --> 08:10.555
The trouble with you, Cratchit,
is that all you think of is pleasure.

08:11.932 --> 08:15.935
Pleasure and squandering money.

08:21.233 --> 08:22.817
You'll, uh...

08:22.985 --> 08:26.487
You'll be wanting the whole day off
tomorrow, I suppose.

08:27.739 --> 08:30.908
- If it's convenient, sir.
- No, sir.

08:31.076 --> 08:33.953
It is not convenient.

08:34.621 --> 08:36.038
And it is not fair.

08:36.832 --> 08:43.129
Yet if I stopped your wages for it,
you'd think yourself ill-used no doubt.

08:43.297 --> 08:48.092
And yet you don't think me ill used
when I pay a day's wages for no work.

08:48.760 --> 08:50.678
Well, it is Christmas day,
Mr. Scrooge.

08:50.846 --> 08:52.680
And it is only once a year, sir.

08:52.889 --> 08:58.436
A poor excuse for picking a man's
pocket every 25th of December.

08:58.604 --> 09:02.356
I don't pay good money for you
to be forever on holiday.

09:02.524 --> 09:05.860
I appreciate your kindness,
Mr. Scrooge.

09:06.028 --> 09:11.240
That's my weakness.
I'm a martyr to my own generosity.

09:11.658 --> 09:15.870
I give you one Christmas day off
and you expect them all.

09:16.038 --> 09:18.831
Very well, take the day.

09:18.999 --> 09:20.124
Thank you, sir.

09:20.292 --> 09:22.835
But be here all the earlier
the next morning.

09:23.045 --> 09:25.755
Yes, sir. I will, sir.
Thank you very much.

09:26.882 --> 09:29.508
Oh, and, uh, Merry Christmas,
Mr. Scrooge.

09:29.718 --> 09:35.181
Be gone from here and take your
infernal Merry Christmas with you.

09:35.390 --> 09:37.058
I beg your pardon, sir.

09:37.225 --> 09:39.018
No offense, sir.

09:46.652 --> 09:48.653
There's another one.

09:49.529 --> 09:53.866
Fifteen shillings a week.
A wife and five children.

09:54.034 --> 09:56.619
Still talks of a Merry Christmas.

10:29.403 --> 10:31.946
[MERCHANT SHOUTING
AND CROWD MURMURING]

10:39.496 --> 10:41.622
Boo. Kathy, my dear.

10:41.790 --> 10:43.666
Tim. Oh.

10:43.834 --> 10:46.335
Oh, you're both frozen.

10:47.170 --> 10:48.254
I'm sorry I'm late.

10:48.422 --> 10:51.841
But Mr. Scrooge and I had a lot
of last-minute business to attend to.

10:52.008 --> 10:55.428
Well, my loves,
which one do you like best, eh?

10:55.595 --> 10:57.513
I like that dolly in the corner.

10:57.681 --> 10:58.931
I like all of them.

10:59.099 --> 11:02.101
Ha, ha. Good boy.
And why not one in particular?

11:02.269 --> 11:04.019
Well, you said
I can't have none of them,

11:04.187 --> 11:05.855
so I might as well like them all.

11:06.022 --> 11:09.692
Tim, you are a philosopher
and a gentleman.

11:09.860 --> 11:12.820
And I've got 15 shillings in my pocket.

11:12.988 --> 11:15.072
BOTH:
Fifteen shillings?

11:15.240 --> 11:17.158
Fifteen shillings.

11:17.325 --> 11:20.119
Which says that the Cratchit family
are gonna have as good a Christmas

11:20.287 --> 11:22.621
as the lord mayor of London himself.

11:22.789 --> 11:26.083
Oh, I do like that dolly in the corner.

11:26.251 --> 11:30.296
[SINGING] Christmas children
Peep into Christmas windows

11:30.922 --> 11:35.092
See a world as pretty as a dream

11:35.927 --> 11:38.345
Christmas trees and toys

11:38.513 --> 11:40.723
Christmas hopes and joys

11:40.891 --> 11:45.770
Christmas puddings
Rich with Christmas cream

11:45.979 --> 11:47.813
[LAUGHING]

11:48.356 --> 11:52.193
Christmas presents shine
In the Christmas windows

11:53.028 --> 11:57.072
Christmas boxes
Tied with pretty bows

11:57.824 --> 12:00.284
Wonder what's inside

12:00.494 --> 12:02.495
What delights they hide

12:02.662 --> 12:05.915
But 'til Christmas morning
No one knows

12:06.124 --> 12:08.542
You with five children, Bob.
Five for a shilling.

12:08.710 --> 12:09.794
Thank you, John.

12:10.003 --> 12:15.299
[SINGING]
Won't it be exciting if it snows?

12:24.434 --> 12:28.312
I suppose that children everywhere

12:28.480 --> 12:31.315
Will say a Christmas prayer

12:31.525 --> 12:36.529
'Til Santa brings
Their Christmas things

12:37.322 --> 12:40.199
There, my loves. I've bought you
the finest bird in the shop.

12:40.367 --> 12:42.660
Well, for one and ten pence
ha' penny.

12:42.828 --> 12:46.705
[SINGING] Christmas children
Live in a Christmas daydream

12:47.833 --> 12:51.919
Waiting for the magic to unfold

12:52.838 --> 12:55.089
Wondrous things to eat

12:55.257 --> 12:57.800
Every Christmas treat

12:58.009 --> 13:02.096
Rich or not
The Christmas pot of gold

13:03.014 --> 13:07.977
Hypnotizes children young and old

13:16.444 --> 13:18.779
[MERCHANT SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY]

13:21.616 --> 13:22.700
Quite right, Mr. Cratchit.

13:22.868 --> 13:25.536
With your lot to feed,
apples at six a penny are the best bet.

13:25.704 --> 13:27.538
I'd rather have the dolly in the corner.

13:27.706 --> 13:30.207
I'd rather have the oranges.

13:30.417 --> 13:34.169
And 1846 is the best vintage
in 20 years.

13:34.337 --> 13:35.838
At that price it should be.

13:36.006 --> 13:37.798
- Your change, sir.
- Thank you, Mr. Bissett.

13:37.966 --> 13:40.968
- And a happy Christmas to you.
BISSETT: Happy Christmas to you, sir.

13:41.136 --> 13:43.304
This will make the finest quality punch,
Mr. C.

13:43.471 --> 13:44.722
And only tuppence a pint.

13:44.890 --> 13:48.851
Christmas punch,
it's a Cratchit specialty.

13:49.352 --> 13:50.436
[KIDS LAUGH]

13:51.813 --> 13:53.856
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

13:59.529 --> 14:01.697
Four pence for a Christmas pudding.

14:01.865 --> 14:03.282
Scandalous.

14:06.244 --> 14:08.078
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

14:08.246 --> 14:10.372
JOHN: It's Papa.
- Where is he?

14:10.540 --> 14:12.750
Here we are, my loves.
Look what we've brought for you.

14:12.959 --> 14:15.044
And about time too, Bob Cratchit.

14:15.211 --> 14:17.588
We were beginning to think
you'd all gone away for Christmas.

14:18.131 --> 14:21.508
[SINGING] Christmas children
Hunger for Christmas morning

14:22.385 --> 14:23.427
Thank you.

14:23.595 --> 14:27.139
Christmas day's a wonder to behold

14:28.558 --> 14:31.560
Young ones' dreams come true

14:31.728 --> 14:34.730
Not so young ones too

14:36.566 --> 14:41.028
I believe that story we've been told

14:41.196 --> 14:42.988
You're not the only ones
who have been busy.

14:43.156 --> 14:45.866
Come and see
what we've been up to.

14:46.576 --> 14:56.418
Christmas is for children
Young and old

15:19.526 --> 15:22.444
MAN 1: Uh, good evening.
MAN 2: Good evening, sir.

15:24.114 --> 15:27.866
Have we the pleasure of addressing
Mr. Scrooge or Mr. Marley?

15:28.034 --> 15:31.954
It's no pleasure to me, sir,
to be addressed by either of you.

15:32.122 --> 15:34.915
And Mr. Marley has been dead
these seven years.

15:35.083 --> 15:37.876
Seven years ago
this very night he died.

15:38.044 --> 15:39.628
We've no doubt his liberality

15:39.796 --> 15:42.548
is well represented
by his surviving partner.

15:42.716 --> 15:43.799
[MAN 1 CHUCKLES]

15:43.967 --> 15:45.259
Uh, Mr. Scrooge.

15:45.427 --> 15:48.887
Uh, sir, at this festive season
of the year, sir,

15:49.055 --> 15:51.390
it is more than usually desirable, uh,

15:51.558 --> 15:53.726
that we should make
some slight provision

15:53.893 --> 15:55.227
for the poor and the destitute.

15:55.395 --> 15:57.229
Excellent. Then I suggest you do so.

15:57.439 --> 15:59.648
You miss our point, sir.

15:59.816 --> 16:02.401
The poor suffer greatly
at the present time.

16:02.569 --> 16:04.862
Many thousands
are in want of common necessaries.

16:05.071 --> 16:07.698
- Are there no prisons?
- Oh, indeed there are, sir.

16:07.866 --> 16:09.658
That's something
there's no shortage of.

16:09.868 --> 16:11.744
And the workhouses,
are they still in operation?

16:11.911 --> 16:13.871
They are, sir.
I wish I could say they were not.

16:14.080 --> 16:15.164
I'm very glad to hear it.

16:15.331 --> 16:17.458
For a moment I was afraid
that something had occurred

16:17.625 --> 16:20.127
to stop them in their useful purpose.

16:20.295 --> 16:21.962
MAN 1:
Oh, but, sir.

16:22.130 --> 16:24.506
A few of us
are endeavoring to raise a fund

16:24.674 --> 16:26.884
to buy the poor some meat and drink
and means of warmth.

16:27.052 --> 16:28.302
We choose this time, sir,

16:28.470 --> 16:32.056
because it is a time when want
is keenly felt and abundance rejoices.

16:32.223 --> 16:34.516
- What may we put you down for, sir?
- Nothing, sir.

16:34.726 --> 16:36.185
MAN 1:
Ah, you wish to be anonymous.

16:36.352 --> 16:40.064
I wish to be left alone, sir.
That is what I wish.

16:40.231 --> 16:42.066
I don't make myself merry
at Christmas

16:42.233 --> 16:45.069
and I cannot afford
to make idle people merry.

16:45.236 --> 16:46.653
I have been forced to support

16:46.821 --> 16:49.031
the establishments I have mentioned
through taxation.

16:49.199 --> 16:51.325
And God knows
they cost more than they are worth.

16:51.493 --> 16:53.410
Those who are badly off
must go there.

16:53.578 --> 16:55.037
Many would rather die than go there.

16:55.205 --> 16:57.247
If they would rather die
then they had better do it

16:57.415 --> 17:00.000
and decrease the surplus population.

17:00.168 --> 17:02.920
Good night, gentlemen.

17:03.713 --> 17:05.672
Humbug.

17:06.299 --> 17:10.010
Poppycock. Balderdash. Bah.

17:10.178 --> 17:12.054
[SINGING]
Scavengers and sycophants

17:12.222 --> 17:14.431
And flatterers and fools

17:14.598 --> 17:18.602
Pharisees and parasites
And hypocrites and ghouls

17:18.811 --> 17:22.689
Calculating swindlers
Prevaricating frauds

17:22.857 --> 17:26.443
Perpetrating evil
As they roam the earth in hordes.

17:26.611 --> 17:30.030
Feeding on their fellow men
Reaping rich rewards

17:30.198 --> 17:32.908
Contaminating everything they see

17:33.993 --> 17:35.953
Corrupting honest men

17:37.455 --> 17:38.539
Like me

17:38.706 --> 17:41.166
[SHOUTING AND MURMURING]

17:48.758 --> 17:55.097
I hate people

17:57.058 --> 17:59.059
People are despicable creatures.

17:59.227 --> 18:01.061
Loathsome, inexplicable creatures

18:01.229 --> 18:02.980
Good for nothing, kickable creatures

18:03.148 --> 18:04.898
I hate people

18:07.569 --> 18:09.027
I abhor them

18:11.156 --> 18:14.908
When I see the indolent classes
Sitting on their indolent arses

18:15.076 --> 18:16.869
Gulping ale from indolent glasses

18:17.036 --> 18:18.996
I hate people

18:21.499 --> 18:23.000
I detest them

18:23.585 --> 18:25.252
I deplore them

18:25.461 --> 18:28.922
MERCHANT 1:
Knives, scissors or razors to grind.

18:29.090 --> 18:31.091
SCROOGE [SINGING]:
Fools who have no money spend it

18:31.259 --> 18:33.093
Get in debt then try to end it

18:33.261 --> 18:34.887
Beg me on their knees befriend them

18:35.054 --> 18:36.555
Knowing I have cash to lend them

18:36.723 --> 18:38.974
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

18:39.559 --> 18:41.518
Softhearted me

18:42.395 --> 18:44.229
Hard-working me

18:45.064 --> 18:50.944
Clean-living, thrifty
And kind as can be

18:52.822 --> 19:00.662
Situations like this
Are of interest to me

19:02.248 --> 19:03.874
It's Mr. Scrooge.

19:04.042 --> 19:07.419
MERCHANT 1:
Knives, scissors or razors to grind.

19:07.587 --> 19:10.005
Two pounds, 5 shillings, ladies.
Due before Christmas.

19:10.173 --> 19:11.256
That means today.

19:11.424 --> 19:12.925
But you see, Mr. Scrooge, sir,

19:13.092 --> 19:14.801
we've been giving more credit
than usual.

19:15.011 --> 19:16.136
That's your business, madam.

19:16.304 --> 19:19.139
Mine is to collect
2 pounds, 5 shillings now.

19:19.349 --> 19:21.058
We sell things for children, sir.

19:21.226 --> 19:23.393
At this time of the year
people can't afford to pay.

19:23.603 --> 19:26.313
Neither can I afford it, madam.

19:26.481 --> 19:31.360
However, I will allow you
an extra week's credit.

19:31.569 --> 19:33.528
BOTH:
Oh, thank you, Mr. Scrooge.

19:33.696 --> 19:38.909
Which will only cost you
a further 12 shillings.

19:39.077 --> 19:40.619
Twelve. Oh, but, Mr. Scrooge.

19:40.787 --> 19:43.288
But we scarcely make
that much in a week.

19:43.498 --> 19:47.334
If you would prefer me to confiscate
your store and its contents,

19:47.502 --> 19:50.337
which is my legal right, I will do so.

19:50.964 --> 19:52.673
- But we will pay, sir.
- We will pay, sir.

19:52.840 --> 19:54.466
You'll both sign this.

19:54.634 --> 19:58.720
MERCHANT 1:
Knives, scissors or razors to grind.

19:58.888 --> 20:03.308
- And you can give me a pair of these.
WOMAN 1: Certainly, Mr. Scrooge.

20:03.768 --> 20:07.104
Oh, look, there's that lovable
Father Christmas again.

20:07.313 --> 20:09.481
MOTHER: Merry Christmas, sir.
A penny for the baby, sir.

20:09.649 --> 20:10.857
[SCROOGE GRUMBLES]

20:11.025 --> 20:12.734
A penny for the baby, sir.

20:12.944 --> 20:14.653
MERCHANT 2:
Lavender. Sweet lavender.

20:14.821 --> 20:16.655
[SINGING]
I hate people

20:16.823 --> 20:19.157
I loathe people

20:19.325 --> 20:22.828
I despise and abominate people

20:22.996 --> 20:25.038
Move over.

20:25.206 --> 20:27.207
Life is full of cretinous wretches

20:27.375 --> 20:29.209
Earning what
Their sweatiness fetches

20:29.377 --> 20:31.295
Empty minds
Whose pettiness stretches

20:31.462 --> 20:33.505
Further than I can see

20:35.466 --> 20:36.591
Little wonder

20:37.427 --> 20:39.261
I hate people

20:41.347 --> 20:44.766
And I don't care if they hate me

20:44.976 --> 20:46.810
[ALL BOOING]

20:48.646 --> 20:49.896
[KIDS LAUGHING]

20:57.030 --> 20:58.572
Not now, Mr. Scrooge, please.

20:58.740 --> 21:01.033
Two pounds 7 and 6, Miller.

21:01.200 --> 21:02.784
And now is as good a time as any.

21:02.994 --> 21:04.369
[IN SQUEAKY VOICE]
Stop it, stop it.

21:04.537 --> 21:06.621
- But I'm performing.
- You're always performing.

21:06.789 --> 21:09.624
- Where's my money?
- Tomorrow for sure, Mr. Scrooge.

21:09.792 --> 21:11.335
After the Christmas morning show.

21:11.502 --> 21:13.045
It's my best day of the year.

21:13.254 --> 21:16.465
Tomorrow it will be 2 pounds 10
or I confiscate your puppets.

21:16.674 --> 21:19.343
All right, Mr. Scrooge.
Two pounds 10.

21:19.552 --> 21:23.013
[IN SQUEAKY VOICE]
Oh, what a pity. What a pity.

21:25.683 --> 21:29.519
BOYS [SINGING]:
Father Christmas, Father Christmas

21:29.687 --> 21:31.938
He's the meanest man
In the whole wide world

21:32.106 --> 21:33.857
In the whole wide world
You can feel it

21:34.734 --> 21:37.402
- He's a miser
- He's a skinflint

21:37.570 --> 21:38.612
SCROOGE:
Bah.

21:38.780 --> 21:39.988
He's a stingy lout

21:40.156 --> 21:42.324
Leave your stocking out
For your Christmas gift

21:42.492 --> 21:44.117
And he'll steal it

21:44.327 --> 21:48.080
It's a shame he's a villain

21:48.247 --> 21:56.713
What a game for a villain
To play on Christmas day

21:56.923 --> 22:01.259
Hark the herald angels sing
Glory to the...

22:01.427 --> 22:03.095
Thank you, guv'nor.

22:03.262 --> 22:04.638
Father Christmas
Father Christmas

22:04.806 --> 22:06.390
Will be just as mean
As he's ever been

22:06.557 --> 22:09.476
And I'm here to say
We should all send Father Christmas

22:09.644 --> 22:11.103
Get out of here.

22:11.270 --> 22:13.021
On his Merry Christmas way

22:13.189 --> 22:14.398
Come on.

22:14.565 --> 22:16.566
[BOYS CHATTERING]

22:16.734 --> 22:18.485
[WHISTLES]

22:18.945 --> 22:21.321
PHILLIP:
Wait for me.

22:26.285 --> 22:30.163
Father Christmas
Father Christmas

22:30.331 --> 22:32.457
He's the rottenest man
In the universe

22:32.625 --> 22:34.418
There's no one worse, you can tell it

22:35.545 --> 22:38.505
- He's a rascal
- He's a bandit

22:38.714 --> 22:41.133
- Scum.
- Come along.

22:41.300 --> 22:42.342
He's a crafty one

22:42.552 --> 22:44.845
Leave your door undone
He'll go in your house

22:46.472 --> 22:47.556
And sell it

22:47.723 --> 22:49.474
MAN:
Here's your money, sir. Pray count it.

22:49.684 --> 22:53.103
You waste breath, sir.
No one has ever short-changed me.

22:53.271 --> 22:55.105
[BOYS CHEER]

22:56.858 --> 22:58.191
It's a crime

22:58.776 --> 23:00.360
It's a scandal

23:00.570 --> 23:08.743
What a game for a vandal to play
On Christmas day

23:20.423 --> 23:21.965
SCROOGE:
Beat it.

23:27.388 --> 23:29.306
TOM: Merry Christmas, sir.
Merry Christmas.

23:29.474 --> 23:30.807
[CHUCKLES]

23:30.975 --> 23:34.269
MERCHANT 2:
Lavender. Sweet lavender.

23:34.979 --> 23:37.189
Sweet lavender.

23:39.734 --> 23:41.234
Hot broth, Mr. Scrooge,

23:41.402 --> 23:46.323
a small token of Christmas esteem
with the compliments of Tom Jenkins.

23:46.491 --> 23:47.574
No.

23:47.742 --> 23:50.869
And there'll be a free can of broth, sir,
every night for the coming year

23:51.037 --> 23:55.373
in gratitude for your infinite kindness
in giving me another two weeks to pay.

23:55.583 --> 23:56.917
One week.

23:57.126 --> 23:59.294
- Ten days?
- One week.

24:00.171 --> 24:02.088
- One week.
- And put a lid on that stuff.

24:02.256 --> 24:03.340
I'll take it home.

24:04.884 --> 24:08.803
[SINGING]
If you distrust Father Christmas

24:08.971 --> 24:10.764
It's as well to know
That we told you so

24:10.932 --> 24:14.184
Because I'm here to say
We should all send Father Christmas

24:14.352 --> 24:15.894
SCROOGE:
Beat it.

24:18.272 --> 24:22.317
- Father Christmas
- Father Christmas

24:22.527 --> 24:27.906
On his Merry Christmas way

24:30.409 --> 24:32.786
[DOG BARKING NEARBY]

24:54.684 --> 24:58.353
Scrooge.

24:58.521 --> 25:00.188
Marley?

25:32.054 --> 25:33.680
Humbug.

25:53.743 --> 25:56.119
[BELLS JINGLING]

26:06.756 --> 26:11.593
Merry Christmas, guv'nor.
Merry Christmas.

26:13.137 --> 26:16.348
Merry Christmas.

27:22.164 --> 27:23.623
[WIND HOWLING]

27:23.791 --> 27:29.170
MARLEY:
Scrooge.

27:33.300 --> 27:35.343
It's humbug still.

27:36.512 --> 27:38.847
I'll not believe it.

27:49.108 --> 27:51.443
[FAINT LAUGHTER]

28:10.087 --> 28:12.172
[BELL RINGING]

28:33.152 --> 28:35.445
[CLOCKS CHIMING]

28:40.159 --> 28:42.410
[RINGING AND CHIMING
INTENSIFIES]

28:51.462 --> 28:53.713
[RINGING AND CHIMING STOPS]

29:13.526 --> 29:15.318
Huh.

29:16.195 --> 29:17.987
[CHAINS CLANGING NEARBY]

29:20.699 --> 29:22.534
[GRUMBLES]

29:42.888 --> 29:47.892
MARLEY:
Scrooge.

30:35.900 --> 30:37.692
How now.

30:38.569 --> 30:40.486
What do you want with me?

30:40.654 --> 30:42.655
MARLEY:
Much.

30:43.449 --> 30:44.532
Who are you?

30:44.700 --> 30:54.459
In life, I was your partner,
Jacob Marley.

30:56.712 --> 30:58.504
Can you sit down?

30:59.048 --> 31:02.258
Of course I can sit down.

31:02.426 --> 31:04.427
SCROOGE:
Do so then.

31:15.022 --> 31:16.773
[SCROOGE SCOFFS]

31:21.487 --> 31:24.614
You don't believe in me, do you?

31:25.324 --> 31:27.158
No, I don't.

31:27.326 --> 31:32.538
Why do you doubt
the evidence of your own eyes?

31:33.832 --> 31:38.294
Because I've had a slight
stomach disorder.

31:39.380 --> 31:42.465
It's undoubtedly affected my vision.

31:43.550 --> 31:45.843
You're an hallucination.

31:46.387 --> 31:52.600
Probably brought on
by an undigested bit of beef

31:52.768 --> 31:58.106
or a blob of mustard,
or a crumb of cheese or an old potato.

31:59.024 --> 32:00.984
Yes, that's what you are.

32:01.193 --> 32:02.902
You are an old potato.

32:04.488 --> 32:06.447
You do not exist, Jacob Marley.

32:07.199 --> 32:09.158
It's humbug I tell you.

32:09.326 --> 32:10.368
It's a lot of...

32:10.536 --> 32:13.162
[WAILS]

32:19.837 --> 32:21.462
No! I beseech you!

32:21.630 --> 32:22.964
Stop!

32:23.173 --> 32:26.050
Now do you believe in me?

32:26.260 --> 32:28.845
I believe in you absolutely.

32:29.013 --> 32:30.596
But why do you walk the earth?

32:30.764 --> 32:32.932
Why do you come to persecute me?

32:33.100 --> 32:36.769
And what is that great chain
you wear?

32:36.979 --> 32:40.398
I wear the chain I forged in life.

32:40.566 --> 32:49.282
I made it link by link
and yard by yard while on Earth.

32:49.450 --> 32:52.660
And now I'll never be rid of it

32:52.828 --> 32:58.666
any more than you
will ever be rid of yours.

32:59.835 --> 33:00.877
Mine?

33:01.045 --> 33:05.923
It was as heavy and long
as this seven Christmases ago.

33:06.133 --> 33:12.889
It's a terrible ponderous chain
you are making, Scrooge.

33:13.098 --> 33:16.434
Tell me more, Marley,
but speak comfort to me.

33:16.602 --> 33:19.353
- I have none to give.
- None?

33:19.521 --> 33:24.484
Comfort comes from other sources,
Ebenezer Scrooge.

33:24.651 --> 33:32.742
And is given by other ministers than I
to other kinds of men than you.

33:32.910 --> 33:36.913
When I lived, my spirit, like yours,

33:37.081 --> 33:42.460
never walked beyond the narrow limits
of our counting house.

33:42.628 --> 33:46.297
But you were always
a good man of business.

33:46.465 --> 33:51.385
Mankind should be our business,
Ebenezer.

33:51.553 --> 33:59.519
But we seldom attend to it,
as you shall see.

34:04.858 --> 34:08.277
Marley!

34:08.529 --> 34:10.571
[SCROOGE WHIMPERING]

34:11.532 --> 34:14.617
Marley. Marley.

34:25.795 --> 34:30.675
[SINGING] See the phantoms
Filling the sky around you

34:30.842 --> 34:35.721
They astound you I can tell

34:36.514 --> 34:41.893
These inhabitants of hell

34:45.149 --> 34:49.527
Poor wretches
Whom the hand of heaven ignores

34:50.404 --> 34:54.322
Beware
Beware

34:54.491 --> 34:56.242
Beware

34:57.411 --> 35:04.876
Lest their dreadful fate be yours

35:51.340 --> 35:52.965
It was a dream.

35:53.133 --> 35:55.009
[CHUCKLES]

35:55.177 --> 35:58.471
Yes, that's what it was. A dream.

35:59.973 --> 36:04.352
It's not a dream, Ebenezer.

36:04.519 --> 36:07.480
For pity's sake, Marley.
Leave me in peace.

36:07.648 --> 36:11.192
It was for pity's sake I came here.

36:11.401 --> 36:14.070
Pity for you.

36:14.238 --> 36:23.287
I leave you with just the tiniest chance
of escaping my fate.

36:23.497 --> 36:27.166
You were always
a good friend to me, Jacob. Thank you.

36:28.252 --> 36:33.130
You will be visited by three ghosts.

36:33.840 --> 36:35.925
I... I think I'd rather not.

36:36.134 --> 36:39.971
The first will appear tonight
when the bell tolls 1.

36:40.180 --> 36:45.351
Couldn't I take them all at once,
and get it over with, Jacob?

36:45.560 --> 36:47.812
The second at 2:00.

36:47.980 --> 36:55.278
And the third when the bell tolls 3.

36:55.445 --> 36:58.114
- I must go now.
- Marley, wait.

36:58.323 --> 37:01.701
I'm doomed to wander
through the world

37:01.868 --> 37:06.247
in everlasting repentance.

37:07.499 --> 37:10.835
Remember
what has passed between us.

37:12.212 --> 37:16.424
Farewell, Scrooge.

38:11.396 --> 38:13.564
Three ghosts? Ha.

38:13.732 --> 38:16.067
Three humbugs.

38:57.025 --> 38:59.068
[GROANS]

39:23.218 --> 39:25.219
[CLOCK CHIMING]

39:30.559 --> 39:32.393
Half past 10?

39:33.979 --> 39:36.105
Quarter to 11?

39:39.943 --> 39:41.235
One o'clock?

39:41.486 --> 39:43.612
[CLOCK BELL CHIMES]

39:46.658 --> 39:47.700
Who are you?

39:47.868 --> 39:51.328
I am the spirit
whose coming was foretold to you.

39:56.710 --> 39:59.628
- You don't look like a ghost.
- Thank you.

40:00.297 --> 40:03.007
May I enquire more precisely
who or what you are?

40:03.383 --> 40:06.302
I am the Ghost of Christmas Past.

40:06.470 --> 40:09.555
- Long past?
- No, your past.

40:09.723 --> 40:12.808
- What business brings you here?
- Your welfare.

40:13.018 --> 40:15.102
To be woken by a ghost
at 1:00 in the morning

40:15.270 --> 40:17.646
is hardly conducive to my welfare.

40:17.856 --> 40:20.399
Your redemption, then.

40:22.402 --> 40:25.029
Rise and walk with me.

40:26.990 --> 40:28.449
Where are we going?

40:28.658 --> 40:31.494
We are going to look
at your childhood.

40:31.661 --> 40:35.789
KIDS [SINGING]:
Sing a song of gladness and cheer

40:35.957 --> 40:40.044
For the time of Christmas is here

40:40.253 --> 40:43.839
Look around about you and see

40:44.591 --> 40:48.761
What a world of wonder
This world can be

40:48.929 --> 40:53.015
Sing a Christmas carol
Sing a Christmas carol

40:53.183 --> 40:58.521
Sing a Christmas carol
Like the children do

40:58.688 --> 41:02.900
Enjoy the beauty
All the joy and beauty

41:03.109 --> 41:05.069
That a Merry Christmas
Can bring to you

41:05.237 --> 41:06.946
Do you remember these children?

41:07.113 --> 41:09.365
Of course. All of them.

41:09.574 --> 41:11.492
London bridge is falling down
My fair lady

41:11.660 --> 41:13.160
For the time of Christmas is here

41:13.370 --> 41:16.288
Sing a song of sixpence
A pocket full of rye

41:16.498 --> 41:17.873
Look around about you and see

41:18.041 --> 41:22.336
Here we go round the mulberry bush
On a cold and frosty morning

41:22.921 --> 41:25.798
Look, there's my little sister.

41:26.007 --> 41:28.842
- Fran. Fran.
- Sing a Christmas carol

41:29.052 --> 41:30.928
Fran!

41:31.096 --> 41:32.888
Why doesn't she wave back?

41:33.056 --> 41:35.099
She cannot see you.

41:35.267 --> 41:38.602
These are but shadows
of the things that have been.

41:38.937 --> 41:43.440
That a Merry Christmas
Can bring to you

41:43.858 --> 41:47.403
I could never join
in those Christmas parties.

41:47.571 --> 41:51.156
The school is not quite empty, is it?

41:51.658 --> 41:57.830
A solitary boy neglected by his family
is left there still.

42:19.853 --> 42:21.103
Poor boy.

42:23.815 --> 42:25.274
I wish...

42:25.442 --> 42:28.694
- What is it?
- Ugh, nothing, nothing.

42:28.862 --> 42:30.237
What is it you wish?

42:30.405 --> 42:33.073
There were some boys
singing a Christmas carol

42:33.241 --> 42:35.117
outside my door last night.

42:35.285 --> 42:37.661
I should have given them something,
that's all.

42:37.829 --> 42:40.581
Let us look at another Christmas.

42:44.002 --> 42:46.503
Ebby. Dear, dear brother.

42:46.671 --> 42:48.881
- I've come to bring you home.
- Home with you, Fran?

42:49.049 --> 42:51.175
Father is so much kinder
than he used to be.

42:51.384 --> 42:53.719
He sent me in a coach
to bring you home, Ebby.

42:53.928 --> 42:56.388
We're to be together
all Christmas long.

42:56.556 --> 42:59.099
Go and fetch your things.

42:59.309 --> 43:03.145
Always a delicate creature
whom a breath might have withered.

43:03.647 --> 43:06.148
But she had a large heart.

43:06.358 --> 43:08.233
She had. I'll not deny it.

43:08.401 --> 43:12.196
She died a woman
and I believe had children.

43:12.364 --> 43:14.365
One child.

43:14.532 --> 43:17.034
Your nephew.

43:17.202 --> 43:18.744
Yes.

43:19.954 --> 43:24.249
There is a Christmas
that you really enjoyed.

43:28.129 --> 43:31.882
Why, it's old Fezziwig alive again.

43:32.050 --> 43:33.509
I was his apprentice.

43:35.512 --> 43:37.721
Yo-ho, Ebenezer. Yo-ho, Dick.

43:37.889 --> 43:41.141
Hi-de-ho and chirrup.
No more work today, me boys.

43:43.144 --> 43:46.313
Hi-de-hi, it's Christmas Eve, Dick.
It's Christmas, Ebenezer.

43:46.481 --> 43:49.692
Now come on, clear everything away
before a man can say Jack Robinson.

43:49.859 --> 43:52.236
And make some room here
before Mrs. Fezziwig

43:52.404 --> 43:55.155
and my daughters arrive
with the punchbowl.

43:55.323 --> 43:57.741
SCROOGE: My word,
I am a good-looking chap. Ha.

43:57.909 --> 44:01.662
And strong too.
I used to carry sacks around all day.

44:01.871 --> 44:03.539
And that other fellow.

44:03.707 --> 44:05.666
I remember him. Dick Wilkins.

44:05.875 --> 44:07.710
Nice young fellow.
Very attached to me he was.

44:07.877 --> 44:09.420
Dear, oh, dear.

44:09.587 --> 44:11.505
[SHOUTING AND LAUGHING]

44:11.673 --> 44:13.507
VIOLINIST:
Hey!

44:15.218 --> 44:17.469
Hey!

44:25.979 --> 44:28.147
FEZZIWIG:
Mrs. Fezziwig.

44:28.314 --> 44:30.232
[LAUGHS]

44:31.484 --> 44:33.026
Me very dear friends.

44:33.236 --> 44:36.530
There will now be happiness
and contentment in this room,

44:36.698 --> 44:39.199
the like of which none of us
has ever seen before.

44:39.367 --> 44:40.868
Begin.

44:41.035 --> 44:42.828
[ALL CHEER]

44:44.706 --> 44:48.250
[SINGING] Of all the days
In all the year that I'm familiar with

44:48.460 --> 44:50.169
There's only one that's really fun

44:50.336 --> 44:52.129
ALL: December the 25th
- Correct

44:52.338 --> 44:55.924
Ask anyone called Robinson
Or Brown or Jones or Smith

44:56.092 --> 44:57.760
Their favorite day and they will say

44:57.969 --> 45:00.053
ALL: December the 25th
- Correct

45:00.263 --> 45:03.515
December the 25th, my dears
December the 25th

45:03.725 --> 45:06.560
The dearest day in all the year

45:07.562 --> 45:09.772
- December the 25th
- Correct

45:15.236 --> 45:17.446
December the 25th

45:20.992 --> 45:22.785
FEZZIWIG:
Mrs. Fezziwig.

45:22.994 --> 45:24.453
- December the 25th
- Correct

45:24.662 --> 45:28.415
At times we're glad to see the back
Of all our kin and kith

45:28.625 --> 45:30.292
But there's a date we celebrate

45:30.502 --> 45:32.252
ALL: December the 25th
- Correct

45:32.462 --> 45:36.089
At times our friends may seem
To be devoid of wit and pith

45:36.299 --> 45:38.008
But all of us are humorous

45:38.218 --> 45:40.344
ALL: December the 25th
- Correct

45:40.553 --> 45:43.764
December the 25th, my dears
December the 25th

45:43.973 --> 45:47.643
The dearest day in all the year

45:47.852 --> 45:49.728
December the 25th

45:49.896 --> 45:51.772
[ALL LAUGHING]

45:57.362 --> 45:58.987
Why didn't you join the dance?

45:59.197 --> 46:01.156
Because I couldn't do it.

46:01.324 --> 46:02.950
[GHOST TSKS]

46:16.714 --> 46:20.092
December the 25th, my dears
December the 25th

46:20.260 --> 46:23.971
The dearest day in all the year

46:24.138 --> 46:27.266
- December the 25th
- Correct.

46:29.936 --> 46:33.522
If there's a day in history
That's more than any myth

46:33.690 --> 46:35.440
Beyond a doubt, one day stands out

46:35.608 --> 46:37.568
ALL: December the 25th
- Correct

46:37.777 --> 46:41.154
I don't hear any arguments
So may I say forthwith

46:41.322 --> 46:44.867
- I wish that every day could be
ALL: December the 25th

46:45.076 --> 46:46.994
FEZZIWIG:
Hey.

46:47.745 --> 46:49.037
Go on.

46:49.205 --> 46:50.497
[ALL CHEER]

46:50.665 --> 46:53.041
Now, go on, go on. Go on.

46:53.209 --> 46:54.835
[ALL CHEER]

46:55.962 --> 46:57.296
Oh, me?

46:58.006 --> 46:59.715
[LAUGHING]

47:06.848 --> 47:08.473
What a marvelous man.

47:08.641 --> 47:10.267
What's so marvelous?

47:10.435 --> 47:13.312
He's merely spent a few pounds
of your mortal money,

47:13.479 --> 47:15.230
three or four perhaps.

47:15.398 --> 47:17.691
What is that to be deserving
of so much praise?

47:17.859 --> 47:19.067
You don't understand.

47:19.235 --> 47:21.570
He has the power
to make us happy or unhappy,

47:21.738 --> 47:23.864
to make our work
a pleasure or a burden.

47:24.032 --> 47:27.159
It's nothing to do with money.

47:34.500 --> 47:38.170
December the 25th, my dears
December the 25th

47:38.379 --> 47:42.049
The dearest day in all the year

47:42.216 --> 47:52.017
December the 25th, my dears

47:52.185 --> 47:53.477
[FEZZIWIG LAUGHS]

47:53.645 --> 48:00.859
December the 25th, my dears

48:12.580 --> 48:14.247
Isabel.

48:14.415 --> 48:17.000
Fezziwig's daughter.

48:17.835 --> 48:20.963
You were going to marry her,
weren't you?

48:21.965 --> 48:23.632
Yes.

48:41.693 --> 48:47.781
[SINGING]
You, you were new to me

48:48.116 --> 48:52.494
You, you were spring

48:53.538 --> 48:59.126
You, you were true to me

48:59.293 --> 49:04.965
You, you were everything

49:40.877 --> 49:45.589
[SINGING] They say happiness
Is a thing you can't see

49:45.757 --> 49:49.217
A thing you can't touch, I disagree

49:49.385 --> 49:50.802
FEZZIWIG:
Hi-de-ho.

49:51.763 --> 49:53.722
- Here we are.
- Yoo-hoo. Yoo-hoo.

49:57.935 --> 50:01.730
Happiness is standing beside me

50:01.939 --> 50:07.903
I can see him, he can see me

50:11.282 --> 50:17.329
Happiness is whatever
You want it to be

50:23.211 --> 50:27.089
Happiness is a high hill

50:27.256 --> 50:30.342
Will I find it? Yes, I will

50:30.510 --> 50:34.471
Happiness is a tall tree

50:34.639 --> 50:36.473
Can I climb it?

50:36.641 --> 50:42.312
Watch and see

50:53.324 --> 50:58.036
They say happiness
Is the folly of fools

50:58.204 --> 51:02.457
Pity poor me, one of the fools

51:05.211 --> 51:08.880
Happiness is smiling upon me

51:09.048 --> 51:15.595
Walking my way, sharing my day

51:16.430 --> 51:21.476
Happiness is whatever
You want it to be

51:24.564 --> 51:28.608
Happiness is a bright star

51:28.776 --> 51:33.280
Are we happy? Yes, we are

51:33.489 --> 51:40.745
Happiness is a clear sky

51:41.080 --> 51:49.045
Give me wings and let me fly

51:49.213 --> 51:54.801
Let me fly

51:55.011 --> 51:56.803
[HORSE NEIGHS]

51:58.014 --> 52:01.600
For happiness

52:01.767 --> 52:11.776
Is whatever you want it to be

52:18.326 --> 52:24.331
SCROOGE [SINGING]:
You, you were good for me

52:25.249 --> 52:28.710
You were my day

52:31.380 --> 52:35.884
Did all you could for me

52:36.302 --> 52:41.765
I let you go away

52:46.520 --> 52:48.480
I did love her, you know.

52:48.648 --> 52:52.984
- Did you?
- Oh, yes, I loved her.

52:53.486 --> 52:55.946
Then why did you let her go?

52:56.113 --> 52:59.241
I've never been quite sure.

52:59.408 --> 53:01.493
Then let us go and see.

53:10.002 --> 53:12.879
- Ebenezer?
- Yeah?

53:13.965 --> 53:15.340
I've come to say goodbye.

53:16.926 --> 53:19.678
I am going away, Ebenezer.
You will not see me again.

53:19.845 --> 53:22.097
But you were gonna marry me.

53:22.264 --> 53:23.640
No.

53:25.059 --> 53:27.310
You have found another love
to replace me.

53:27.478 --> 53:30.772
She's much more desirable
than I am.

53:30.940 --> 53:34.025
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

53:36.487 --> 53:38.738
This lady here.

53:41.033 --> 53:43.994
How shall I ever
understand this world?

53:44.745 --> 53:47.080
There is nothing
on which it is so hard as poverty

53:47.248 --> 53:49.791
and yet, there is nothing it condemns
with such severity

53:49.959 --> 53:51.084
as the pursuit of wealth.

53:51.293 --> 53:54.254
You fear the world too much,
Ebenezer.

53:54.422 --> 53:58.883
All your nobler dreams that I loved
I've seen die off one by one

53:59.385 --> 54:01.386
until only the desire for gain is left.

54:01.554 --> 54:03.596
I'm not changed towards you, am I?

54:03.764 --> 54:05.849
Yes, you are.

54:06.017 --> 54:09.769
Your promise to me was made when
you were poor and content to be so.

54:10.354 --> 54:12.939
- You were someone else then.
- I was a boy.

54:13.149 --> 54:14.190
You see?

54:14.358 --> 54:18.945
Your own feelings tell you
that you are not what you were.

54:19.447 --> 54:21.990
I see that all too clearly.

54:22.867 --> 54:26.202
And so I can release you.

54:26.537 --> 54:28.329
Have I ever asked to be released?

54:28.497 --> 54:30.290
In words, no.

54:30.458 --> 54:32.959
But in a changed nature, yes.

54:33.169 --> 54:36.463
In everything that made my love
of value to you, yes.

54:38.340 --> 54:40.842
If you met me today,
you would not love me.

54:41.010 --> 54:42.635
- I would, I do.
- Shh.

54:42.803 --> 54:45.346
- I still do.
- I'm trying to listen.

54:46.140 --> 54:50.018
Isabel, I find it impossible to discuss
personal affairs during business hours.

54:50.186 --> 54:52.312
Now, please.

54:58.069 --> 54:59.444
ISABEL:
You see?

54:59.612 --> 55:02.989
If you weigh me by gain,
I weigh very little.

55:03.157 --> 55:04.657
And so I am not enough for you.

55:05.451 --> 55:09.037
And I release you with a full heart
for the love of him you once were.

55:09.205 --> 55:11.915
Say something, you fool.
Say something.

55:12.124 --> 55:15.794
You may, for a little while,
have pain in this, but it will pass.

55:16.170 --> 55:20.507
And you will dismiss the recollection
of it gladly as an unprofitable dream

55:20.716 --> 55:23.676
from which it happened
well that you awoke.

55:26.055 --> 55:28.848
OLD SCROOGE:
Don't go, it's a mistake. Don't go.

55:29.016 --> 55:31.893
Be happy in the life you have chosen.

55:32.061 --> 55:33.436
OLD SCROOGE:
Isabel.

55:34.188 --> 55:35.980
Isabel?

55:38.109 --> 55:39.442
Isabel.

55:39.610 --> 55:41.277
[DOOR CLOSES]

55:52.456 --> 55:53.790
You fool.

55:56.460 --> 55:58.962
[SINGING]
You fool

56:02.299 --> 56:05.593
I let you go away

56:07.972 --> 56:12.976
And now I can see

56:13.853 --> 56:18.314
Now you're a dream gone by

56:19.275 --> 56:24.404
Oh, how could there be

56:25.406 --> 56:32.620
Such a fool as I?

56:36.250 --> 56:40.044
I who must travel on

56:41.338 --> 56:44.716
What hope for me?

56:45.801 --> 56:51.639
Dream where my past has gone

56:52.683 --> 56:55.602
Live with a memory

56:59.440 --> 57:04.611
You, my only hope

57:05.321 --> 57:10.200
You, my only love

57:11.785 --> 57:17.040
You, you

57:21.629 --> 57:24.297
You

57:30.846 --> 57:34.015
Spirit, remove me from this place.

57:34.183 --> 57:37.518
I can bear it no more.

57:37.728 --> 57:39.812
[CLOCK TICKING]

57:51.033 --> 57:52.825
[SOBBING]

58:12.638 --> 58:15.890
Stupid old fool.

58:18.477 --> 58:22.272
Getting yourself all upset
over nothing.

58:23.482 --> 58:26.025
It's all in your imagination.

58:29.446 --> 58:31.614
[CLOCK CHIMING]

58:40.040 --> 58:44.085
The first at 1, the second at 2.

58:53.721 --> 58:56.723
I'm ready for you, wherever you are.

59:03.272 --> 59:04.814
Nothing.

59:05.691 --> 59:08.943
[LAUGHTER]

59:21.665 --> 59:25.043
GHOST:
Ebenezer Scrooge.

59:27.921 --> 59:30.840
Come here, Scrooge.
I'm waiting for you.

59:31.050 --> 59:33.301
Or shall I come in there and get you?

59:34.053 --> 59:35.511
I'm coming.

59:37.348 --> 59:38.723
I'm coming, I'm coming.

59:47.524 --> 59:49.400
GHOST:
Welcome, Scrooge.

59:50.194 --> 59:51.778
Is it too bright for you?

01:00:05.876 --> 01:00:10.421
Come over here, you weird little man.

01:00:10.798 --> 01:00:14.550
I am the Spirit of Christmas Present.

01:00:17.096 --> 01:00:19.097
Now look upon me.

01:00:19.264 --> 01:00:21.808
You have never seen
the like of me before.

01:00:22.393 --> 01:00:23.434
Never.

01:00:23.602 --> 01:00:26.479
Yet, how many of my brothers
have you rejected

01:00:26.647 --> 01:00:28.648
in your miserable lifetime?

01:00:28.816 --> 01:00:31.692
I have never met any
of your brothers, sir.

01:00:31.860 --> 01:00:33.945
You have never looked for them.

01:00:34.113 --> 01:00:35.988
Well, how many of them are there?

01:00:36.156 --> 01:00:37.698
What year is this?

01:00:37.866 --> 01:00:39.617
1860.

01:00:39.827 --> 01:00:43.162
Then I have 1, 859 brothers.

01:00:43.330 --> 01:00:48.376
Each year at this time,
one of us visits this puny little planet

01:00:48.544 --> 01:00:52.797
to spread some happiness,
and to remove as many as we can

01:00:52.965 --> 01:00:55.091
of the causes of human misery.

01:00:55.759 --> 01:00:59.720
Which is why I have come to see you,
Ebenezer Scrooge.

01:00:59.888 --> 01:01:02.056
[SCROOGE YELLS]

01:01:03.058 --> 01:01:05.435
You're a funny-looking little creature.

01:01:05.602 --> 01:01:09.021
I must admit, I found it hard to believe
you'd be as horrible

01:01:09.189 --> 01:01:11.107
as my brothers said you'd be.

01:01:11.275 --> 01:01:15.069
But now that I look at you, I can see
they were understating the truth.

01:01:15.237 --> 01:01:19.115
Let me assure you that I am a man
of the highest principles

01:01:19.283 --> 01:01:21.033
and the most generous spirit.

01:01:21.243 --> 01:01:24.162
Generous spirit? You?

01:01:24.329 --> 01:01:26.998
You don't know the meaning
of the phrase.

01:01:27.166 --> 01:01:29.167
But you're about to find out.

01:01:30.586 --> 01:01:33.963
Now, drink this.

01:01:36.175 --> 01:01:38.593
- What is it?
- Taste it.

01:01:41.722 --> 01:01:43.306
SCROOGE:
Mm.

01:01:43.765 --> 01:01:44.807
Mm.

01:01:44.975 --> 01:01:46.767
Do you like it?

01:01:48.437 --> 01:01:51.606
It's wonderful.
I've never tasted anything like it.

01:01:51.773 --> 01:01:53.399
Of course you haven't.

01:01:53.567 --> 01:01:57.236
- What is it?
- The milk of human kindness.

01:01:57.404 --> 01:01:59.489
There are more good things
in this life, Scrooge,

01:01:59.656 --> 01:02:01.324
than you can possibly imagine.

01:02:01.533 --> 01:02:04.118
I'm sure there are.
Can I have some more?

01:02:04.328 --> 01:02:08.956
[SINGING] Ebenezer Scrooge
The sins of man are huge

01:02:09.124 --> 01:02:12.793
A never-ending symphony
Of villainy and infamy

01:02:13.003 --> 01:02:17.131
Duplicity, deceit and subterfuge

01:02:17.341 --> 01:02:21.761
And no one's worse
Than Ebenezer Scrooge

01:02:23.430 --> 01:02:27.725
Though man's a handy candidate
For hell

01:02:27.935 --> 01:02:36.943
I must admit, life sometimes
Has its brighter side as well

01:02:41.073 --> 01:02:44.659
I like life, life likes me

01:02:44.826 --> 01:02:47.912
Life and I fairly fully agree

01:02:48.080 --> 01:02:51.123
Life is fine, life is good

01:02:51.291 --> 01:02:54.585
Especially mine
Which is just as it should be

01:02:54.753 --> 01:02:58.756
I like pouring the wine and why not?

01:02:58.924 --> 01:03:03.803
Life's a pleasure that I deny not

01:03:11.353 --> 01:03:13.646
I like life here and now

01:03:13.814 --> 01:03:16.274
Life and I made a mutual vow

01:03:16.441 --> 01:03:18.734
Till I die, life and I

01:03:18.902 --> 01:03:21.862
We'll both try to be better somehow

01:03:22.030 --> 01:03:25.616
And if life were a woman
She would be my wife

01:03:25.826 --> 01:03:27.243
- Why?
- Why?

01:03:27.411 --> 01:03:29.829
Because I like life

01:03:30.038 --> 01:03:32.415
That's all very well for you,
but not for me.

01:03:32.583 --> 01:03:33.833
I hate life.

01:03:34.042 --> 01:03:36.085
Nonsense, man. Why?

01:03:36.295 --> 01:03:38.629
Because life hates me, that's why.

01:03:38.839 --> 01:03:42.550
Scrooge, you're an even bigger fool
than I took you for.

01:03:42.759 --> 01:03:46.178
I've never heard
such a lot of self-pitying drivel.

01:03:46.346 --> 01:03:48.723
You don't even know how to live.

01:03:48.890 --> 01:03:51.434
Now you listen to me.

01:03:52.311 --> 01:03:54.395
I like life

01:03:55.689 --> 01:03:56.731
Well, go on.

01:03:56.898 --> 01:03:58.649
[SINGING]
I like life

01:03:58.817 --> 01:04:00.151
That's better.

01:04:00.319 --> 01:04:02.403
[SINGING]
Life likes me

01:04:02.571 --> 01:04:04.030
Life likes me

01:04:04.239 --> 01:04:05.448
Good, good.

01:04:05.616 --> 01:04:08.367
I make life a perpetual spree

01:04:08.577 --> 01:04:10.411
A perpetual spree

01:04:10.621 --> 01:04:12.079
Eating food

01:04:12.289 --> 01:04:13.831
Drinking wine

01:04:14.041 --> 01:04:17.084
Thinking who'd like the privilege
To dine me

01:04:17.628 --> 01:04:19.629
I like drinking the drink I'm drinking

01:04:19.796 --> 01:04:21.797
That's better, Scrooge.

01:04:21.965 --> 01:04:26.344
I like thinking the thoughts
I'm thinking

01:04:26.511 --> 01:04:28.512
I like songs, I like dance

01:04:28.680 --> 01:04:30.598
I hear music and I'm in a trance

01:04:30.807 --> 01:04:32.850
- Tra-la-la
- Oom-pa-pa

01:04:33.018 --> 01:04:35.227
Chances are we shall get up
And prance

01:04:35.395 --> 01:04:36.646
[SCROOGE LAUGHS]

01:04:36.813 --> 01:04:41.442
Where there's music and laughter
Happiness is rife

01:04:41.610 --> 01:04:43.611
- Why?
- Why?

01:04:43.779 --> 01:04:47.281
Because I like life

01:04:47.449 --> 01:04:49.450
[SCROOGE LAUGHING
HYSTERICALLY]

01:05:03.799 --> 01:05:06.759
BOTH [SINGING]:
Where there's music and laughter

01:05:06.927 --> 01:05:09.595
Happiness is rife

01:05:09.763 --> 01:05:15.768
Why? Because I like life

01:05:15.977 --> 01:05:22.149
See how much we like life

01:05:26.238 --> 01:05:27.655
[GHOST GRUNTS]

01:05:27.823 --> 01:05:30.408
[GHOST CHUCKLING
AND SCROOGE GRUNTING]

01:05:33.370 --> 01:05:35.538
What happened? What's happened?

01:05:35.706 --> 01:05:39.667
What the devil am I doing in a pile
of snow in the middle of the night?

01:05:39.835 --> 01:05:41.585
That's what I'd like to know.
Where are we?

01:05:41.753 --> 01:05:46.006
Now, Scrooge,
over there lies the lavish home

01:05:46.174 --> 01:05:51.929
of Robert Cratchit, esquire, who owes
both the opulence of his surroundings

01:05:52.139 --> 01:05:54.932
and the magnificence
of his Christmas celebrations

01:05:55.100 --> 01:05:58.436
to the high principles
and generous spirit of his employer.

01:05:58.603 --> 01:06:00.855
Here. I want to look in the window.

01:06:01.022 --> 01:06:04.358
It will cost you nothing, which I'm sure
will be good news for you.

01:06:04.526 --> 01:06:05.651
Will they be able to see me?

01:06:05.819 --> 01:06:08.946
No, which I feel sure
will be good news for them.

01:06:09.114 --> 01:06:11.365
I could do with
another of them drinks.

01:06:11.533 --> 01:06:12.700
Later.

01:06:12.868 --> 01:06:17.580
For the time being, I think it better
you see things as they really are.

01:06:33.388 --> 01:06:35.973
Oh, nectar. Pure nectar.

01:06:36.141 --> 01:06:39.018
And at only tuppence a pint,
you can't really grumble.

01:06:39.186 --> 01:06:42.271
What a tragedy it is that Her Majesty
and His Worship the Lord Mayor

01:06:42.439 --> 01:06:43.564
couldn't be with us tonight.

01:06:43.732 --> 01:06:46.859
They don't know what they're missing.
Now you try that, my love.

01:06:47.652 --> 01:06:49.904
Mm. Bob Cratchit, you're a genius.

01:06:50.113 --> 01:06:52.782
JOY:
The stuffing's ready, father.

01:06:53.074 --> 01:06:57.119
The marriage of roast goose and sage
and onion stuffing à la Cratchit

01:06:57.287 --> 01:06:59.371
is one of the culinary miracles
of our day.

01:06:59.539 --> 01:07:00.664
[MRS. CRATCHIT CHUCKLES]

01:07:00.832 --> 01:07:05.461
And a living legend throughout the
length and breadth of Camden Town.

01:07:05.629 --> 01:07:07.213
Now, the only remaining problem,
my dear,

01:07:07.380 --> 01:07:09.632
is whether to put the stuffing
inside the goose

01:07:09.800 --> 01:07:11.300
or the goose inside the stuffing.

01:07:11.468 --> 01:07:12.510
[KIDS LAUGH]

01:07:12.677 --> 01:07:16.430
But since the ultimate intention
is to put them both inside ourselves,

01:07:16.598 --> 01:07:18.933
I don't suppose it very much matters.

01:07:19.100 --> 01:07:22.978
And here they are, the one and only
carol-singing Cratchits.

01:07:23.146 --> 01:07:26.357
Newly returned
from their triumphant musical tour.

01:07:26.525 --> 01:07:28.025
How did you do, Tiny Tim?

01:07:28.193 --> 01:07:31.612
- Ten pence ha'penny.
- Ooh. Well done.

01:07:31.822 --> 01:07:34.824
Another fantastic coup
by young Timothy Cratchit.

01:07:34.991 --> 01:07:36.492
The financial wizard.

01:07:36.660 --> 01:07:38.869
At only 7 years of age,

01:07:39.037 --> 01:07:43.123
the youngest millionaire
in the vast Cratchit empire.

01:07:43.291 --> 01:07:48.212
Ladies and gentlemen, if I may steal
a moment of your valuable time,

01:07:48.755 --> 01:07:52.258
I would ask you to drink a toast
to the sparkling good health

01:07:52.425 --> 01:07:55.302
of the two gentlemen
whose industry and generosity

01:07:55.470 --> 01:07:59.181
have provided
our sumptuous Christmas repast.

01:07:59.349 --> 01:08:02.268
- Master Timothy Cratchit.
MRS. CRATCHIT: Tim.

01:08:02.477 --> 01:08:04.728
And Mr. Ebenezer Scrooge.

01:08:09.401 --> 01:08:12.069
MRS. CRATCHIT: What are you
trying to do, ruin our Christmas?

01:08:12.237 --> 01:08:14.363
But his money paid for the goose,
my dear.

01:08:14.531 --> 01:08:17.867
No, your money paid for the goose,
my dear.

01:08:18.033 --> 01:08:19.827
But he paid me the money.

01:08:19.995 --> 01:08:22.955
Because you earned it, my love.

01:08:23.122 --> 01:08:25.541
Fifteen shillings a week
at three pence an hour.

01:08:26.084 --> 01:08:28.377
And not a penny rise in eight years.

01:08:28.587 --> 01:08:30.004
Believe me, you earned it.

01:08:30.171 --> 01:08:32.923
Oh, Mr. Scrooge assures me
that times are hard.

01:08:33.091 --> 01:08:34.841
He's right. For you they are.

01:08:35.010 --> 01:08:36.426
But not for himself.

01:08:36.595 --> 01:08:40.139
Well, nonetheless, he is the founder
of our feast and we shall drink to him.

01:08:40.348 --> 01:08:41.390
Quite right.

01:08:41.558 --> 01:08:43.475
You, listen to this.

01:08:43.852 --> 01:08:46.895
The founder of our feast indeed.

01:08:47.063 --> 01:08:48.439
I wish I had him here.

01:08:48.607 --> 01:08:51.692
I'd give him a piece of my mind
to feast upon.

01:08:51.859 --> 01:08:53.652
He'd have indigestion for a month.

01:08:53.862 --> 01:08:57.406
CRATCHIT: Ethel, my dear,
the children. It's Christmas.

01:08:57.616 --> 01:08:58.908
It needs to be Christmas, Bob,

01:08:59.075 --> 01:09:02.411
to drink to a rotten, hard,
stingy old miser like Scrooge.

01:09:02.578 --> 01:09:05.413
- But, Ethel...
- You know he is, Bob.

01:09:05.582 --> 01:09:08.917
Nobody knows it better than you,
my poor love.

01:09:09.085 --> 01:09:10.752
To Christmas, my dear.

01:09:12.255 --> 01:09:15.466
Children,
we shall drink to your father,

01:09:15.634 --> 01:09:18.636
for all the love and happiness
he gives us.

01:09:18.803 --> 01:09:21.138
And to Tiny Tim
for the health we wish him.

01:09:22.640 --> 01:09:24.475
And for the sake of your father,

01:09:24.684 --> 01:09:27.937
I'll even drink to that old miser,
Mr. Scrooge.

01:09:28.647 --> 01:09:31.564
Long life to him and to us all.

01:09:31.774 --> 01:09:33.524
A Merry Christmas to us all.

01:09:33.734 --> 01:09:35.027
Merry Christmas.

01:09:35.194 --> 01:09:36.278
CRATCHIT:
God bless us.

01:09:36.446 --> 01:09:38.154
God bless us, everyone.

01:09:38.323 --> 01:09:39.782
As I said to the Lord Mayor,

01:09:39.950 --> 01:09:43.077
if Her Most Gracious Majesty
is feeling bored, I said,

01:09:43.243 --> 01:09:45.828
you wheel her over to Camden town,
I said.

01:09:45.997 --> 01:09:50.250
A glass of Bob Cratchit's hot punch
and a song from Tiny Tim

01:09:50.417 --> 01:09:52.752
and we'll have her back
on her regal feet in no time.

01:09:52.921 --> 01:09:54.421
[KIDS LAUGH]

01:09:54.589 --> 01:09:55.965
Well, there's your punch.

01:09:56.132 --> 01:09:57.841
Now where's our song, my Tiny Tim?

01:09:58.009 --> 01:09:59.510
KIDS: Tiny Tim.
- Come on, Tim.

01:09:59.719 --> 01:10:00.970
- Song, song now.
- Come on, Tim.

01:10:02.555 --> 01:10:08.560
[SINGING] On a beautiful day
That I dream about

01:10:08.728 --> 01:10:14.233
In a world I would love to see

01:10:14.401 --> 01:10:20.447
Is a beautiful place
Where the sun comes out

01:10:20.615 --> 01:10:26.745
And it shines in the sky for me

01:10:26.913 --> 01:10:32.543
On this beautiful winter's morning

01:10:32.711 --> 01:10:38.465
If my wish could come true somehow

01:10:38.633 --> 01:10:45.514
Then the beautiful day
That I dream about

01:10:45.682 --> 01:10:52.146
Would be here and now

01:11:01.364 --> 01:11:07.327
On this beautiful winter's morning

01:11:07.495 --> 01:11:13.876
If my wish could come true somehow

01:11:14.044 --> 01:11:21.592
Then the beautiful day
That I dream about

01:11:21.760 --> 01:11:26.972
Would be here

01:11:27.140 --> 01:11:31.810
And now

01:11:31.978 --> 01:11:33.228
[ALL CLAPPING]

01:11:33.396 --> 01:11:34.438
CRATCHIT:
Good boy.

01:11:34.606 --> 01:11:38.400
MRS. CRATCHIT:
Well done, Tiny Tim, well done.

01:11:40.820 --> 01:11:42.821
GHOST:
What an unpleasant child.

01:11:42.989 --> 01:11:46.992
You know, Scrooge, there are
few things more nauseating to see

01:11:47.160 --> 01:11:50.204
than a happy family
enjoying themselves at Christmas.

01:11:50.371 --> 01:11:51.955
Do you not agree?

01:11:52.123 --> 01:11:54.583
I think Bob Cratchit's
really rather fond of me.

01:11:54.751 --> 01:11:57.753
Ho-ho-ho. And so is his wife.
Couldn't you tell?

01:11:57.921 --> 01:11:59.338
She doesn't really know me.

01:11:59.506 --> 01:12:02.758
That is one of the few things
wherein fate has blessed her.

01:12:02.926 --> 01:12:06.053
And, uh, what will become
of Tiny Tim?

01:12:06.221 --> 01:12:09.640
What's this?
Concern over a sick child?

01:12:09.808 --> 01:12:11.308
Have you taken leave
of your senses?

01:12:11.476 --> 01:12:12.976
Don't mock me, spirit.

01:12:13.144 --> 01:12:14.686
Is the child very sick?

01:12:14.854 --> 01:12:18.607
Not that it's of any great importance
to me whether he is or not, but is he?

01:12:18.775 --> 01:12:21.026
Well, of course he's sick.

01:12:21.194 --> 01:12:24.446
You mean he's seriously ill?

01:12:28.618 --> 01:12:31.703
Will he live? Well, will he?

01:12:31.913 --> 01:12:35.082
What does it matter to you,
Ebenezer Scrooge?

01:12:35.250 --> 01:12:38.293
If he's going to die,
then he'd better do it

01:12:38.461 --> 01:12:41.839
and decrease the surplus population.

01:12:42.715 --> 01:12:44.550
We have one more call to make.

01:12:44.759 --> 01:12:46.927
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:12:47.095 --> 01:12:50.931
will you please honor me
with your undivided attention?

01:12:51.099 --> 01:12:52.141
The time has come

01:12:52.308 --> 01:12:55.561
that I know you all look forward to
in this house every Christmas Eve,

01:12:55.728 --> 01:12:57.896
when I ask you to drink
to the good health

01:12:58.064 --> 01:13:01.441
and long life
of my celebrated Uncle Ebenezer.

01:13:01.609 --> 01:13:03.402
[DISCONTENTED CLAMOR]

01:13:03.570 --> 01:13:05.445
Sounds to me as
if he knows I'm here.

01:13:05.655 --> 01:13:08.532
Of course he doesn't.
He can't see you.

01:13:08.741 --> 01:13:11.618
Harry, I've visited you every Christmas
for the past five years,

01:13:11.786 --> 01:13:14.913
and to this day I can never understand
this extraordinary ritual

01:13:15.081 --> 01:13:17.583
of toasting the health
of your old Uncle Ebenezer.

01:13:17.792 --> 01:13:20.210
I mean, everybody knows
he's the most miserable old skinflint

01:13:20.378 --> 01:13:21.962
that ever walked God's earth.

01:13:22.130 --> 01:13:26.216
- Who's he?
- Oh, just a friend.

01:13:26.426 --> 01:13:27.926
My dear Tom, it's very simple.

01:13:28.094 --> 01:13:31.013
He is indeed
the most despicable old miser,

01:13:31.181 --> 01:13:33.724
worse than you
could ever possibly imagine.

01:13:33.892 --> 01:13:35.142
[ALL LAUGH]

01:13:35.310 --> 01:13:39.229
- You find this amusing?
- Believe it or not, he likes you.

01:13:39.397 --> 01:13:40.981
HARRY:
You see, I look at it this way:

01:13:41.191 --> 01:13:43.275
If I can wish
a Merry Christmas to him,

01:13:43.443 --> 01:13:46.111
who is beyond dispute
the most obnoxious

01:13:46.279 --> 01:13:48.614
and parsimonious
of all living creatures...

01:13:48.823 --> 01:13:49.865
ALL:
Hear.

01:13:50.033 --> 01:13:52.659
HARRY: Then I know in my heart
that I am truly a man of goodwill.

01:13:52.827 --> 01:13:55.746
- Scoundrel.
- Wait, there's more to come.

01:13:55.955 --> 01:13:58.790
And besides, I like old Scrooge.

01:13:59.000 --> 01:14:01.376
- What did I tell you?
HARRY: Truly I do.

01:14:01.586 --> 01:14:04.338
I can't help feeling
that hidden somewhere deep inside

01:14:04.505 --> 01:14:06.798
that loathsome old carcass of his

01:14:06.966 --> 01:14:09.426
there's a different man fighting
to get out.

01:14:09.636 --> 01:14:11.595
Be careful, he may be worse
than the one you know.

01:14:11.804 --> 01:14:13.305
HARRY:
Oh, God forbid, Tom.

01:14:13.473 --> 01:14:16.475
Anyway, that's the reason I ask him
to come here every Christmas.

01:14:16.643 --> 01:14:19.853
In the forlorn hope that one day
he might pick up enough goodwill

01:14:20.021 --> 01:14:22.189
to raise his clerk's wages
by five shillings a week.

01:14:22.398 --> 01:14:23.440
MAN:
Hear, hear.

01:14:23.608 --> 01:14:25.734
HARRY:
God knows it's high time he did.

01:14:25.902 --> 01:14:27.402
He's playing
with other people's money.

01:14:27.570 --> 01:14:29.363
HARRY'S WIFE:
All right, Harry, that's enough.

01:14:29.530 --> 01:14:32.366
I refuse to have Christmas haunted
by Uncle Ebenezer.

01:14:32.533 --> 01:14:33.575
[ALL CHUCKLE]

01:14:33.743 --> 01:14:35.953
We'll have some dancing
and some music.

01:14:36.120 --> 01:14:39.081
Then we'll play some
splendid party games.

01:14:39.249 --> 01:14:42.167
There's a charming new game
called The Minister's Cat.

01:14:42.335 --> 01:14:43.418
It's very funny.

01:14:43.628 --> 01:14:46.213
You'll all end up getting
very angry when you lose.

01:14:46.381 --> 01:14:51.218
And as for you, nephew,
if you were in my will, I'd disinherit you.

01:14:51.386 --> 01:14:55.681
Scrooge. Come over here.

01:14:56.599 --> 01:14:58.433
You need some more of this.

01:14:58.601 --> 01:15:01.311
Hmph. Raise my clerk's wages.

01:15:01.479 --> 01:15:02.688
[PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

01:15:02.855 --> 01:15:05.232
Mm. Mm.

01:15:05.400 --> 01:15:07.359
[SCROOGE CHUCKLES]

01:15:13.491 --> 01:15:15.492
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

01:15:19.539 --> 01:15:21.540
[CLAPPING]

01:15:27.463 --> 01:15:31.675
I know that tune.
I used to sing it when I was a lad.

01:15:35.888 --> 01:15:37.389
KEN:
The minister's cat is a lonely cat

01:15:37.557 --> 01:15:39.391
GRAHAM:
The minister's cat is a languid cat

01:15:39.559 --> 01:15:41.518
GORDON:
The minister's cat is a lordly cat

01:15:41.728 --> 01:15:43.228
MARY:
The minister's cat is a lazy cat

01:15:43.396 --> 01:15:45.272
GUY:
The minister's cat is a ludicrous cat

01:15:45.440 --> 01:15:47.441
HARRY'S WIFE:
The minister's cat is a lascivious cat

01:15:47.608 --> 01:15:49.443
JAMES:
The minister's cat is a...

01:15:49.610 --> 01:15:51.737
- Too late, you're out.
- Oh, no.

01:15:52.405 --> 01:15:54.031
He's out, he's out.

01:15:54.240 --> 01:15:55.324
He's out.

01:15:55.491 --> 01:15:57.826
You see, they get furious
when they lose. It's lovely.

01:15:58.036 --> 01:16:00.871
He's out, next M. Come on, M, M, M.

01:16:01.372 --> 01:16:02.456
Now M.

01:16:02.623 --> 01:16:04.333
The minister's cat is a marvelous cat

01:16:04.500 --> 01:16:05.917
The minister's cat
is a marmalade cat

01:16:06.085 --> 01:16:08.086
- Marmalade.
- The minister's cat is a miserable cat

01:16:08.254 --> 01:16:10.255
- Miserable.
- The minister's cat is a merciful cat

01:16:10.423 --> 01:16:12.215
- Merciful.
- The minister's cat is a... Uh...

01:16:12.383 --> 01:16:13.633
Merry, say merry.

01:16:13.801 --> 01:16:14.968
[ALL LAUGHING]

01:16:15.136 --> 01:16:17.554
- Oh, damn it.
- I told you to say merry.

01:16:17.722 --> 01:16:20.557
Why are you so stupid?
He's always been stupid.

01:16:20.767 --> 01:16:24.227
- Stop yawning when I'm talking to you.
- What next?

01:16:24.437 --> 01:16:25.771
- N, N.
- N.

01:16:25.938 --> 01:16:28.273
- The minister's cat is a naughty cat
- Quickly, quickly.

01:16:28.441 --> 01:16:30.525
- The minister's cat is a noble cat
- Noble cat.

01:16:30.693 --> 01:16:32.694
- The minister's cat is a nebulous cat
- Nebulous.

01:16:32.862 --> 01:16:35.364
- The minister's cat is a...
- Nasty cat.

01:16:35.531 --> 01:16:38.116
- Oh, no, no.
- Oh, no, no, I'm not out.

01:16:38.284 --> 01:16:41.661
- I was just about to say nasty.
- You fool, it's too late.

01:16:41.829 --> 01:16:44.623
You could have said neglectful,
nervous, nauseating.

01:16:44.791 --> 01:16:46.208
You're out, you're out, you're out.

01:16:46.376 --> 01:16:48.126
The minister's cat is an orange cat

01:16:48.294 --> 01:16:50.962
- The minister's cat is an old cat
- Yes.

01:16:53.716 --> 01:16:57.219
SCROOGE: Look, I was
rather good at it but I... But I didn't...

01:16:58.805 --> 01:17:00.514
Oh, thank you, my boy.

01:17:00.723 --> 01:17:02.099
What a wonderful evening.

01:17:02.266 --> 01:17:05.060
That Minister's Cat game, splendid.

01:17:05.228 --> 01:17:07.145
I thought I was rather good at it.

01:17:07.313 --> 01:17:09.272
Good night, good night. Thank you.

01:17:09.440 --> 01:17:13.443
I can honestly say that I haven't
enjoyed a Christmas as much as this

01:17:13.611 --> 01:17:16.363
since I was a young apprentice
at old Fezziwig's

01:17:16.531 --> 01:17:19.116
so, so many years ago.

01:17:19.283 --> 01:17:20.492
Yes.

01:17:20.660 --> 01:17:23.620
What Christmases we used to have
in those days.

01:17:23.788 --> 01:17:26.665
Fantastic they were.

01:17:26.833 --> 01:17:30.502
He had this daughter.

01:17:30.670 --> 01:17:36.258
Reminded me a little bit
of your mother, she did.

01:17:36.426 --> 01:17:38.635
Her name was Isabel.

01:17:40.221 --> 01:17:41.847
Oh.

01:17:42.515 --> 01:17:44.891
Oh, Isabel.

01:17:45.059 --> 01:17:49.062
WOMAN [SINGING]:
They say happiness

01:17:49.230 --> 01:17:53.817
Is the folly of fools

01:17:53.985 --> 01:18:01.116
Pity poor me, one of the fools

01:18:01.284 --> 01:18:04.327
- Happiness
- Happiness...

01:18:04.912 --> 01:18:08.123
Was standing beside me.

01:18:09.250 --> 01:18:12.127
I could see her

01:18:12.879 --> 01:18:15.881
She could see me

01:18:17.508 --> 01:18:23.180
Happiness is whatever

01:18:23.723 --> 01:18:29.561
You want it to be

01:18:37.945 --> 01:18:41.406
Yes, Scrooge.
I have brought you home.

01:18:41.616 --> 01:18:43.033
You're not going?

01:18:43.242 --> 01:18:46.286
My time upon this little planet
is very brief.

01:18:46.454 --> 01:18:47.871
I must leave you now.

01:18:48.080 --> 01:18:52.083
But we still have so much to talk about,
haven't we?

01:18:52.293 --> 01:18:57.380
There is never enough time to do or
say all the things that we would wish.

01:18:57.548 --> 01:19:02.219
The thing is to try to do as much
as you can in the time that you have.

01:19:02.386 --> 01:19:06.598
- Yes, but...
- Remember, Scrooge, time is short.

01:19:06.766 --> 01:19:10.852
And suddenly,
you're not there anymore.

01:19:11.062 --> 01:19:13.230
SCROOGE:
No, wait. Don't go.

01:19:13.397 --> 01:19:14.981
Don't leave me.

01:19:15.149 --> 01:19:17.025
Where are you?

01:19:17.193 --> 01:19:18.902
Why is it so dark?

01:19:19.070 --> 01:19:20.153
I can't see.

01:19:20.321 --> 01:19:21.988
I can't see, I can't see.

01:19:22.156 --> 01:19:24.241
I can't see, I can't...

01:19:24.408 --> 01:19:26.326
[PANTING]

01:19:27.078 --> 01:19:29.496
Oh, my God. What am I doing here?

01:19:30.706 --> 01:19:33.500
Oh, I'm in bed.
That's what I'm doing here.

01:19:33.668 --> 01:19:36.711
This is where I'm supposed to be
in the middle of the night.

01:19:37.380 --> 01:19:40.048
Was I dreaming again?
I must have been.

01:19:42.260 --> 01:19:44.219
That giant.

01:20:03.948 --> 01:20:06.491
[CLOCK CHIMING NEARBY]

01:20:12.164 --> 01:20:14.624
I must be mad. There are no giants.

01:20:14.792 --> 01:20:16.001
[CLOCK BELL CHIMES]

01:20:16.168 --> 01:20:17.294
There are no ghosts.

01:20:17.461 --> 01:20:18.628
[GASPS]

01:20:32.018 --> 01:20:36.563
Am I in the presence of the Ghost
of Christmas Yet To Come?

01:20:38.190 --> 01:20:40.650
And you are to show me
shadows of the things

01:20:40.818 --> 01:20:42.485
that will happen in the time before?

01:20:42.653 --> 01:20:45.113
Is that so, spirit?

01:20:46.616 --> 01:20:51.786
Ghost of the Future, I fear you more
than any apparition I have seen.

01:20:51.954 --> 01:20:54.789
But as I know your purpose
is to do me good,

01:20:54.957 --> 01:20:57.584
and as I hope to be another man
from what I was,

01:20:57.752 --> 01:21:00.545
I am prepared to bear you company.

01:21:00.713 --> 01:21:01.880
Will you speak to me?

01:21:04.508 --> 01:21:09.554
The night is waning fast
and I know that time is precious to me.

01:21:09.722 --> 01:21:12.724
Lead on, spirit. Lead on.

01:21:12.933 --> 01:21:14.601
[THUNDER CRASHES]

01:21:16.937 --> 01:21:18.772
There you are, me friends.

01:21:18.939 --> 01:21:21.024
Shining as bright
as the happy thoughts

01:21:21.192 --> 01:21:25.070
the mere mention of the name
Scrooge brings to our minds.

01:21:27.073 --> 01:21:29.866
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:21:30.034 --> 01:21:34.579
we are gathered here today because
we are united by a common bond.

01:21:34.747 --> 01:21:36.998
ALL:
Yeah!

01:21:37.166 --> 01:21:41.586
Namely our feelings of gratitude
to Mr. Ebenezer Scrooge.

01:21:41.754 --> 01:21:43.421
[CROWD CHEERS]

01:21:45.424 --> 01:21:49.094
TOM: I don't think any of us
can ever hope to find the words

01:21:49.261 --> 01:21:52.847
to describe the true depth
of our feelings towards him.

01:21:53.015 --> 01:21:55.392
[CHEERING AND CHATTERING]

01:21:55.559 --> 01:21:57.727
Is this the future?

01:21:58.229 --> 01:22:01.898
All right, my friends, all right.
I understand your excitement.

01:22:02.066 --> 01:22:03.900
That's Tom Jenkins,
the hot soup man.

01:22:04.068 --> 01:22:06.528
TOM: We are all overjoyed...
- He owes me 6 pounds.

01:22:06.696 --> 01:22:11.032
I must say he looks uncommonly
happy for someone so deep in debt.

01:22:11.409 --> 01:22:13.493
All these people owe me money.

01:22:13.661 --> 01:22:16.079
They love me and I never knew.

01:22:16.247 --> 01:22:20.250
Kindly hold down your emotions,
if you please.

01:22:20.459 --> 01:22:23.586
- Now, we are all deeply moved.
ALL: Yes.

01:22:23.754 --> 01:22:27.340
And those of us what has been in debt
to Mr. S over all these years

01:22:27.508 --> 01:22:31.177
will never forget
what a rare and beautiful thing

01:22:31.345 --> 01:22:32.595
he has just done for us all.

01:22:32.763 --> 01:22:34.347
- Right?
ALL: Right.

01:22:34.557 --> 01:22:36.433
Three cheers for Mr. Scrooge.

01:22:36.600 --> 01:22:38.435
- Hip, hip, hooray!
ALL: Hooray!

01:22:38.602 --> 01:22:41.187
What did I do? What did I do?

01:22:41.355 --> 01:22:43.481
Whatever it was,
it has made them truly happy,

01:22:43.649 --> 01:22:45.108
and I am the cause.

01:22:45.609 --> 01:22:49.320
My friends, I thank you
from the bottom of my heart.

01:22:49.613 --> 01:22:53.241
I shall remember this moment
until my dying day.

01:22:53.409 --> 01:22:55.034
[CROWD CHEERS]

01:22:55.202 --> 01:22:58.246
ALL [SINGING]:
For he's a jolly good fellow

01:22:58.414 --> 01:23:04.627
For he's a jolly good fellow

01:23:04.795 --> 01:23:06.921
And so say all of us

01:23:07.089 --> 01:23:09.215
[CROWD CHEERS]

01:23:10.468 --> 01:23:13.011
May I say in all humility

01:23:13.179 --> 01:23:15.096
[ALL CHEER]

01:23:15.264 --> 01:23:17.807
I have labored unceasingly
all my life.

01:23:17.975 --> 01:23:19.893
[ALL CHEER]

01:23:20.060 --> 01:23:22.687
To be worthy of this
moving demonstration

01:23:22.855 --> 01:23:24.606
of your feelings towards me.

01:23:24.774 --> 01:23:26.816
[ALL CHEER]

01:23:27.485 --> 01:23:30.195
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:23:30.362 --> 01:23:34.908
on behalf of all the people
who have assembled here

01:23:35.075 --> 01:23:39.662
- I would merely like to mention if I may
ALL: You may.

01:23:39.830 --> 01:23:42.040
[SINGING]
That our unanimous attitude

01:23:42.208 --> 01:23:44.292
Is one of lasting gratitude

01:23:44.502 --> 01:23:47.253
For what our friend
Has done for us today

01:23:47.421 --> 01:23:48.546
[ALL LAUGH]

01:23:48.714 --> 01:23:53.551
And therefore
I would simply like to say

01:23:53.719 --> 01:23:55.386
ALL:
You may.

01:23:56.722 --> 01:24:00.058
Thank you very much

01:24:00.267 --> 01:24:04.521
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:24:04.730 --> 01:24:06.773
I may sound double Dutch

01:24:06.941 --> 01:24:08.942
But my delight is such

01:24:09.109 --> 01:24:12.862
I feel as if a losing war
Has been won for me

01:24:13.072 --> 01:24:17.242
And if I had a flag
I'd hang me flag out

01:24:17.409 --> 01:24:21.120
To add a sort of final victory touch

01:24:21.330 --> 01:24:25.375
But since I left me flag at home
I'll simply have to say

01:24:25.543 --> 01:24:33.049
Thank you very, very, very, much

01:24:33.217 --> 01:24:35.343
[ALL LAUGHING]

01:24:40.099 --> 01:24:43.768
Thank you very much
Thank you very much

01:24:43.936 --> 01:24:48.439
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:24:48.649 --> 01:24:50.483
It sounds a bit bizarre

01:24:50.651 --> 01:24:52.569
But things the way they are

01:24:52.778 --> 01:24:56.406
I feel as if another life's
Begun for me

01:24:57.116 --> 01:25:01.202
And if I had a cannon I would fire it

01:25:01.370 --> 01:25:05.331
To add a sort of celebration touch

01:25:05.499 --> 01:25:09.377
But since I left me cannon at home
I'll simply have to say

01:25:09.545 --> 01:25:16.009
Thank you very, very, very much

01:25:16.176 --> 01:25:24.601
For he's a jolly good fellow

01:25:24.810 --> 01:25:26.686
And so say all of us

01:25:26.854 --> 01:25:30.356
Thank you very much

01:25:30.524 --> 01:25:34.777
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:25:34.987 --> 01:25:39.115
It isn't every day
Good fortune comes me way

01:25:39.283 --> 01:25:43.411
I never thought
The future would be fun for me

01:25:43.579 --> 01:25:44.871
- And if I...
- Hey.

01:25:45.080 --> 01:25:47.415
You've woken my baby.
Will you keep quiet?

01:25:47.625 --> 01:25:48.666
Beg your pardon, lady.

01:25:48.834 --> 01:25:51.920
[SINGING QUIETLY]
And if I had a bugle I would blow it

01:25:52.087 --> 01:25:53.129
Shh.

01:25:53.297 --> 01:25:56.966
[SINGING LOUDER] To add
A sort of how's your father touch

01:25:58.928 --> 01:26:03.222
But since I left my bugle at home
I'll simply have to say

01:26:03.432 --> 01:26:10.480
Thank you very, very, very much

01:26:10.689 --> 01:26:13.900
No, no, dear friends.
It is I who should thank you.

01:26:14.068 --> 01:26:15.985
- Thank you very much
- Thank you very much

01:26:16.153 --> 01:26:17.487
Thank you very much

01:26:17.655 --> 01:26:21.908
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:26:22.076 --> 01:26:23.952
The future looks all right

01:26:24.119 --> 01:26:26.037
In fact it looks so bright

01:26:26.205 --> 01:26:30.249
I feel as if they're polishing
The sun for me

01:26:30.417 --> 01:26:34.754
- And if I had a drum I'd have to...
- If I had a drum I'd have to bang it

01:26:34.964 --> 01:26:38.383
To add a sort of
Humpty Dumpty touch

01:26:38.592 --> 01:26:44.681
But since I left me drummer at home
I'll simply have to say...

01:26:48.686 --> 01:26:51.187
The color hurts my eyes.

01:26:51.355 --> 01:26:55.483
I mustn't show weak eyes
to your father when he gets home.

01:26:56.110 --> 01:26:58.611
- It must be near his time.
- Past it.

01:26:59.238 --> 01:27:02.407
But I think he's walked
a little slower these last few evenings.

01:27:02.616 --> 01:27:05.284
MRS. CRATCHIT: I've known him
walk with Tiny Tim on his shoulder

01:27:05.452 --> 01:27:06.911
very fast indeed.

01:27:07.121 --> 01:27:11.124
But he was light to carry
for it was no trouble, no trouble.

01:27:11.583 --> 01:27:13.835
Where is Tiny Tim?

01:27:19.466 --> 01:27:21.426
Take me to him.

01:27:27.016 --> 01:27:33.021
TINY TIM [SINGING FAINTLY]:
On this beautiful winter's morning

01:27:33.188 --> 01:27:39.652
If my wish could come true somehow

01:27:39.820 --> 01:27:47.326
Then the beautiful day
That I dream about

01:27:47.494 --> 01:27:52.957
Would be here

01:27:53.167 --> 01:27:57.795
And now

01:28:04.219 --> 01:28:06.721
I must go now, my little fellow.

01:28:07.556 --> 01:28:10.516
I promised your mother
I'd help her with the Christmas dinner.

01:28:11.894 --> 01:28:14.812
I'll come and see you again
tomorrow.

01:28:14.980 --> 01:28:16.606
Same time.

01:28:17.441 --> 01:28:18.775
All right?

01:28:21.445 --> 01:28:23.071
[SOBBING]
Oh, Tim.

01:28:42.424 --> 01:28:44.717
Poor Tiny Tim.

01:28:47.221 --> 01:28:49.847
Spirit, you've shown me
a Christmas yet to come

01:28:50.015 --> 01:28:54.018
that mingles great happiness
with great sadness.

01:28:54.353 --> 01:28:57.355
But what is to become of me?

01:29:16.542 --> 01:29:19.210
No, no. Please, I beg you.

01:29:19.753 --> 01:29:22.046
I've seen the error of my ways.
I will repent.

01:29:22.214 --> 01:29:24.507
Truly, I will repent!

01:29:26.343 --> 01:29:29.303
[SCREAMING]

01:29:35.185 --> 01:29:37.478
Help! Help!

01:29:37.646 --> 01:29:44.026
Help, help!

01:30:25.903 --> 01:30:28.404
[RUMBLING]

01:30:32.659 --> 01:30:34.660
[SNIFFS]

01:30:35.829 --> 01:30:37.914
[MUTTERS]

01:30:43.003 --> 01:30:44.879
[GRUNTS]

01:31:05.442 --> 01:31:06.984
[SIZZLES]

01:31:13.951 --> 01:31:17.078
VOICE:
Ah.

01:31:18.288 --> 01:31:21.123
So there you are.

01:31:23.627 --> 01:31:25.544
Marley.

01:31:26.505 --> 01:31:27.672
Where am I?

01:31:27.839 --> 01:31:30.800
I should have thought it was obvious.

01:31:30.968 --> 01:31:34.679
I heard you were coming down today,
so I thought I'd come to greet you.

01:31:34.846 --> 01:31:36.555
Show you to your quarters.

01:31:36.723 --> 01:31:38.766
[SCREAMING NEARBY]

01:31:39.810 --> 01:31:41.936
Nobody else wanted to.

01:31:42.104 --> 01:31:44.188
[SCROOGE WHIMPERING]

01:31:45.232 --> 01:31:48.818
That's very civil of you, Marley.

01:31:51.113 --> 01:31:56.158
- I am dead, aren't I?
- As a coffin nail.

01:31:56.827 --> 01:31:58.953
[CLANKING]

01:32:00.205 --> 01:32:03.874
- I'd rather hoped I'd end up in heaven.
- Did you indeed?

01:32:04.042 --> 01:32:09.755
You may find your office here
rather small, but not, I trust, unfamiliar.

01:32:09.923 --> 01:32:10.965
Office?

01:32:11.133 --> 01:32:14.552
Your activities in life
were so pleasing to Lucifer,

01:32:14.720 --> 01:32:18.639
that he has appointed you
to be his personal clerk.

01:32:18.807 --> 01:32:20.558
A singular honor.

01:32:20.726 --> 01:32:26.105
You will be to him, so to speak,
what Bob Cratchit was to you.

01:32:26.273 --> 01:32:28.649
That's not fair. Aah! It's...

01:32:28.817 --> 01:32:30.693
- It's...
- Diabolical.

01:32:30.861 --> 01:32:35.698
I must confess
I find it not altogether unamusing.

01:32:35.866 --> 01:32:40.202
Here we are, my dear Ebenezer.

01:32:40.370 --> 01:32:42.538
[BELL RINGS]

01:32:42.706 --> 01:32:45.541
Your office.

01:33:09.066 --> 01:33:12.777
It's freezing cold in here.

01:33:12.944 --> 01:33:17.448
Lucifer turned the heat off.
He thought it might make you drowsy.

01:33:17.616 --> 01:33:21.786
You'll be the only man in hell
who's chilly.

01:33:21.953 --> 01:33:26.290
Watch out for the rats.
They nibble things.

01:33:26.500 --> 01:33:28.125
Rats?

01:33:28.293 --> 01:33:30.169
[WHIMPERING]

01:33:30.837 --> 01:33:32.004
MARLEY:
Oh.

01:33:33.507 --> 01:33:36.008
I almost forgot.

01:33:36.176 --> 01:33:37.927
I knew there was something.

01:33:38.095 --> 01:33:40.137
They apologize that your

01:33:40.305 --> 01:33:41.931
[CLANKING NEARBY]

01:33:42.099 --> 01:33:45.643
Chain wasn't ready for your arrival.

01:33:45.811 --> 01:33:47.269
It's so big,

01:33:47.479 --> 01:33:51.857
they had to take on extra devils
at the foundry to finish it.

01:33:52.067 --> 01:33:57.488
It's even bigger
than I thought it would be.

01:33:57.656 --> 01:33:58.697
Oh.

01:33:58.865 --> 01:33:59.907
[SNICKERS]

01:34:00.075 --> 01:34:01.742
Here it is now.

01:34:17.008 --> 01:34:21.053
Don't let them do this to me, Marley.
I beg you.

01:34:38.447 --> 01:34:42.032
That's quite a chain, isn't it?

01:34:42.242 --> 01:34:44.618
Help me. Help me.

01:34:44.828 --> 01:34:48.122
Bah, humbug.

01:34:48.290 --> 01:34:49.874
Merry Christmas.

01:34:50.542 --> 01:34:52.877
Don't leave me, Marley.

01:34:53.587 --> 01:34:55.004
Help!

01:34:55.172 --> 01:34:56.922
Help, help!

01:34:57.090 --> 01:35:05.097
Help, help, help!

01:35:06.099 --> 01:35:07.933
Help!

01:35:08.268 --> 01:35:10.436
[GASPING]

01:35:16.151 --> 01:35:17.860
Where am I?

01:35:19.905 --> 01:35:21.947
I'm in my own room.

01:35:23.700 --> 01:35:26.160
I'm not in hell at all.

01:35:26.328 --> 01:35:29.205
I haven't got any chains.

01:35:30.415 --> 01:35:33.834
Perhaps it didn't happen after all.

01:35:36.963 --> 01:35:38.923
Perhaps it did.

01:35:41.426 --> 01:35:43.761
But I'm alive.

01:35:45.805 --> 01:35:48.390
I'm alive.

01:35:49.643 --> 01:35:55.856
I've got a chance to change
and I will not be the man I was.

01:35:58.401 --> 01:36:00.569
I'll begin again.

01:36:00.987 --> 01:36:03.614
I will build my life.

01:36:03.782 --> 01:36:08.702
I will live to know
that I've fulfilled my life.

01:36:09.120 --> 01:36:11.413
I'll begin today.

01:36:11.581 --> 01:36:13.791
Throw away the past,

01:36:13.959 --> 01:36:19.797
and the future I build
will be something that will last.

01:36:25.428 --> 01:36:30.891
I will take the time I have left to live

01:36:31.059 --> 01:36:35.437
and I will give it all
that I have left to give.

01:36:36.565 --> 01:36:41.860
[SINGING]
I will live my days for my fellow men

01:36:42.028 --> 01:36:46.574
And I'll live in praise
Of that moment when

01:36:46.741 --> 01:36:55.583
I was able to begin again

01:37:00.964 --> 01:37:03.966
I will start anew

01:37:04.384 --> 01:37:07.011
I will make amends

01:37:07.178 --> 01:37:13.809
And I'll make quite certain
That the story ends

01:37:14.644 --> 01:37:21.066
On a note of hope
On a strong amen

01:37:21.526 --> 01:37:27.948
And I'll thank the world
And remember when

01:37:28.116 --> 01:37:30.909
I was able to

01:37:31.119 --> 01:37:40.044
Begin again

01:37:40.295 --> 01:37:41.879
[LAUGHING]

01:37:42.047 --> 01:37:44.423
I don't know what to do.

01:37:44.591 --> 01:37:47.760
Yes, begin again.

01:37:48.470 --> 01:37:51.555
I'm as light as a feather.

01:37:53.224 --> 01:37:56.769
I'm as happy as an angel.

01:37:58.104 --> 01:38:01.982
I'm as giddy as a drunken man.

01:38:04.235 --> 01:38:07.863
A Merry Christmas, everybody.

01:38:10.700 --> 01:38:16.372
Oh, Jacob Marley, wherever you are,
you shall see a change in me, Jacob.

01:38:16.539 --> 01:38:18.749
I swear it.

01:38:18.917 --> 01:38:20.292
[LAUGHING AND YELLING]

01:38:33.682 --> 01:38:36.475
Boy. Boy, boy, what day is it?

01:38:36.685 --> 01:38:38.102
- Today?
- Today.

01:38:38.269 --> 01:38:39.853
Why, Christmas day, of course.

01:38:40.063 --> 01:38:44.233
It's Christmas day.
I haven't missed it.

01:38:44.401 --> 01:38:46.110
The spirits have done it all
in one night.

01:38:46.277 --> 01:38:48.320
Well, they can do what they like,
you see.

01:38:48.488 --> 01:38:51.740
Of course they can.
Of course they can. Ha, ha.

01:38:51.908 --> 01:38:53.826
- Hello, my fine young fellow.
- Hello.

01:38:53.993 --> 01:38:56.036
Do you know the butcher's
in the next street but one?

01:38:56.204 --> 01:38:57.246
I should hope so.

01:38:57.414 --> 01:38:59.873
What a remarkable boy.
An intelligent boy.

01:39:00.041 --> 01:39:02.501
Do you happen to know
if they've sold the prize turkey

01:39:02.669 --> 01:39:04.002
that was hanging up in the window?

01:39:04.170 --> 01:39:06.463
Not the big one, the enormous one.

01:39:06.673 --> 01:39:08.132
What, you mean the one
as big as me?

01:39:08.299 --> 01:39:10.175
Ha, ha. What a wonderful boy.

01:39:10.343 --> 01:39:12.094
So witty. It's a pleasure to talk to him.

01:39:12.303 --> 01:39:14.138
- Yes, that's the one.
- It's still there.

01:39:14.347 --> 01:39:15.389
It is? Go and buy it.

01:39:15.557 --> 01:39:17.808
- What's that?
- Here's two sovereigns.

01:39:17.976 --> 01:39:20.853
Go and wake up the butcher
and tell him to open his shop.

01:39:21.020 --> 01:39:22.688
Meet me there in ten minutes.

01:39:22.856 --> 01:39:26.066
Be holding that turkey
and I'll give you a half a crown.

01:39:26.234 --> 01:39:28.902
Go on, run. Run, run.

01:39:29.070 --> 01:39:31.822
Run, run.

01:39:32.824 --> 01:39:35.075
Oh, what a lovely boy.

01:39:35.243 --> 01:39:37.453
I think I'm gonna like children.

01:39:37.662 --> 01:39:41.707
Now, that's what I call a turkey.
It's twice the size of Tiny Tim.

01:39:41.875 --> 01:39:44.585
Come on, dear boy.
Let's go and open the toy shop.

01:39:44.753 --> 01:39:47.296
Thank you. Merry Christmas.

01:39:48.631 --> 01:39:51.800
And I'll have that and some of those.

01:39:51.968 --> 01:39:55.053
And the hobby horse,
and then some flutes and...

01:39:55.221 --> 01:39:57.973
And some trumpets.

01:39:58.141 --> 01:40:00.267
And that doll.

01:40:00.435 --> 01:40:02.352
- And some bows and arrows.
- Bow and arrows.

01:40:02.520 --> 01:40:05.105
Yes and... Oh, yes, and I...

01:40:05.273 --> 01:40:07.149
- I must have a cricket bat.
- Ha, ha.

01:40:07.317 --> 01:40:09.860
And these, and these.

01:40:10.069 --> 01:40:11.653
And a horse and a spinning top.

01:40:11.821 --> 01:40:13.530
And a piano.

01:40:13.698 --> 01:40:15.365
And... And all those dolls.

01:40:15.533 --> 01:40:17.451
- All of them?
- Yes.

01:40:17.619 --> 01:40:19.036
I like that one.

01:40:19.204 --> 01:40:21.163
Oh, and this beautiful coach.

01:40:21.331 --> 01:40:24.875
- And several kites and the horse.
- Yes, yes.

01:40:25.043 --> 01:40:27.336
- And these boats.
- Yes.

01:40:27.504 --> 01:40:29.671
And some of these.

01:40:30.548 --> 01:40:31.840
Oh!

01:40:35.386 --> 01:40:36.720
I'll have that.

01:40:36.888 --> 01:40:38.430
Now, how much is all this?

01:40:38.640 --> 01:40:40.891
- Oh. Uh... Oh.
- Well, never mind.

01:40:41.059 --> 01:40:43.769
Here are some sovereigns
and you can keep the change.

01:40:43.937 --> 01:40:45.729
Oh, thank you, Mr. Scrooge.

01:40:45.939 --> 01:40:48.649
And I shall require
the services of several small boys

01:40:48.817 --> 01:40:52.444
to help to transport these
delightful objects to their destination.

01:40:52.612 --> 01:40:55.030
And each boy shall receive
a half a crown.

01:40:55.240 --> 01:40:57.449
Half a crown, yes, Mr. Scrooge.

01:40:57.617 --> 01:41:00.494
Mr. Scrooge, what has happened?

01:41:02.205 --> 01:41:05.415
What happened is perfectly simple,
Pringle.

01:41:05.583 --> 01:41:08.961
I've discovered that I like life.

01:41:09.170 --> 01:41:11.004
[KIDS LAUGHING]

01:41:14.676 --> 01:41:15.926
[SINGING]
I like life

01:41:16.094 --> 01:41:17.261
Life likes me

01:41:17.428 --> 01:41:19.721
Life and I fairly fully agree

01:41:19.889 --> 01:41:21.098
Life is fine

01:41:21.266 --> 01:41:22.432
Life is good

01:41:22.600 --> 01:41:26.353
Especially mine
Which is just as it should be

01:41:26.688 --> 01:41:31.108
I like pouring the wine and why not?

01:41:31.651 --> 01:41:36.280
Life's a pleasure that I deny not

01:41:36.656 --> 01:41:39.032
I like life, here and now

01:41:39.200 --> 01:41:41.451
Life and I made a mutual vow

01:41:41.619 --> 01:41:46.707
Till I die, life and I
We'll both try to be better somehow

01:41:47.876 --> 01:41:52.045
And if life were a woman
She would be my wife

01:41:52.213 --> 01:41:54.089
[KIDS LAUGH]

01:41:59.095 --> 01:42:00.137
Why?

01:42:00.305 --> 01:42:03.432
Because I like life

01:42:03.600 --> 01:42:05.392
[KIDS CHEER]

01:42:06.686 --> 01:42:07.811
SCROOGE:
Oh, look, a slide.

01:42:07.979 --> 01:42:11.523
No, let me. Let me, let me.

01:42:17.447 --> 01:42:18.989
[YELLS THEN GRUNTS]

01:42:19.157 --> 01:42:21.867
[ALL LAUGHING]

01:42:24.871 --> 01:42:25.996
[SINGING]
I like life

01:42:26.164 --> 01:42:27.247
Life likes me

01:42:27.415 --> 01:42:29.833
I'll make life a perpetual spree

01:42:30.001 --> 01:42:32.252
Eating food, drinking wine

01:42:32.420 --> 01:42:35.047
Thinking who'll have the privilege
To dine me

01:42:35.214 --> 01:42:39.551
I like living the life of pleasure

01:42:39.719 --> 01:42:45.057
Pausing only to take my leisure

01:42:47.310 --> 01:42:49.603
I like songs, I like dance

01:42:49.771 --> 01:42:52.064
I hear music and I'm in a trance

01:42:52.231 --> 01:42:54.691
[PLAYING PLEASANT MELODY]

01:42:57.153 --> 01:42:59.571
Tra-la-la, oom-pa-pa

01:42:59.739 --> 01:43:02.324
Chances are I shall get up and prance

01:43:02.492 --> 01:43:04.576
[SCROOGE HUMMING]

01:43:07.163 --> 01:43:11.291
Where's there's music and laughter
Happiness is rife

01:43:11.459 --> 01:43:12.918
KIDS: Why?
- Why?

01:43:13.086 --> 01:43:17.130
Because I like life

01:43:29.644 --> 01:43:31.436
Uncle Ebenezer.

01:43:32.772 --> 01:43:36.400
Oh, Merry Christmas to you,
my dear nephew.

01:43:36.567 --> 01:43:38.527
And to your enchanting wife.

01:43:38.695 --> 01:43:41.947
We were just on our way
to your house with some presents.

01:43:42.115 --> 01:43:43.782
These are for you.

01:43:43.950 --> 01:43:47.536
From an old fool who deeply regrets
the Christmases gone by

01:43:47.704 --> 01:43:50.580
that he might have shared with you,
and...

01:43:50.748 --> 01:43:57.004
This is for you, my dear.
A sort of belated wedding present.

01:43:57.171 --> 01:44:00.632
Oh, Uncle Ebenezer, thank you.

01:44:01.259 --> 01:44:05.053
Christmas lunch is sharp at 3.
May we expect you?

01:44:08.057 --> 01:44:09.975
You may.

01:44:10.893 --> 01:44:15.105
I'll be there. Oh, you are a pretty girl.

01:44:19.110 --> 01:44:21.111
[ALL SINGING]
I like songs, I like dance

01:44:21.279 --> 01:44:23.530
I hear music and I'm in a trance

01:44:23.698 --> 01:44:25.907
Tra-la-la, oom-pa-pa

01:44:26.075 --> 01:44:29.786
Chances are
I shall get up and prance

01:44:31.039 --> 01:44:35.417
Where there's music and laughter
Happiness is rife

01:44:35.835 --> 01:44:36.877
Why?

01:44:37.045 --> 01:44:39.588
Because I like life

01:44:40.173 --> 01:44:45.802
Father Christmas

01:44:45.970 --> 01:44:48.388
He's the greatest man
In the whole wide world

01:44:48.556 --> 01:44:51.016
In the whole wide world
And he knows it

01:44:51.184 --> 01:44:55.479
Every Christmas, Father Christmas

01:44:55.646 --> 01:44:57.564
Puts a great big sack
On his dear old back

01:44:57.732 --> 01:45:00.400
Because he loves us all
And he knows it

01:45:00.568 --> 01:45:04.738
And he goes for a sleigh ride

01:45:04.906 --> 01:45:09.076
If it snows, then he may ride all night

01:45:09.243 --> 01:45:13.872
But that's all right

01:45:18.169 --> 01:45:20.003
[LAUGHING]

01:45:29.138 --> 01:45:32.349
KIDS:
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

01:45:33.643 --> 01:45:37.604
SCROOGE:
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

01:45:37.814 --> 01:45:40.065
Hey, hey, hey.

01:45:40.233 --> 01:45:42.150
KIDS: In the morning
SCROOGE: In the morning

01:45:42.318 --> 01:45:44.611
KIDS: Christmas morning
SCROOGE: Christmas morning

01:45:44.821 --> 01:45:46.696
If you lift your eyes
There's a big surprise

01:45:46.864 --> 01:45:51.493
On your bed you'll see
There's a gift from Father Christmas

01:45:51.661 --> 01:45:55.622
From Father Christmas

01:45:55.790 --> 01:46:01.378
- That's how Christmas ought to be
- Ha, ha. Hey!

01:46:01.546 --> 01:46:03.547
Merry Christmas.

01:46:03.756 --> 01:46:08.051
A Merry Christmas to you, sir,
from Father Christmas himself.

01:46:08.261 --> 01:46:09.636
MRS. CRATCHIT:
Oh, dear.

01:46:09.846 --> 01:46:11.972
Don't worry about your goose,
Mrs. Cratchit.

01:46:12.140 --> 01:46:14.641
You can use it as stuffing for this.

01:46:16.394 --> 01:46:18.436
Now, where are the other presents?

01:46:18.646 --> 01:46:23.608
This dolly is for you, my dear.
And this one is for you.

01:46:23.776 --> 01:46:27.696
And this pretty little dolly is for you.

01:46:27.864 --> 01:46:29.698
It's the dolly in the corner.

01:46:29.866 --> 01:46:31.074
[SCROOGE CHUCKLES]

01:46:31.242 --> 01:46:35.162
- And those are for you, my boy.
- Thank you.

01:46:35.329 --> 01:46:41.001
And these, Bob Cratchit,
are for you and your good lady.

01:46:41.169 --> 01:46:42.502
I must leave you now.

01:46:42.712 --> 01:46:44.629
As you can imagine,
it's a very busy day for me.

01:46:44.839 --> 01:46:48.175
And I have many more calls to make.

01:46:49.010 --> 01:46:53.180
Ah! I almost forgot.

01:46:54.891 --> 01:46:56.266
[KIDS CHATTERING]

01:46:56.434 --> 01:46:59.895
This is for you.

01:47:01.939 --> 01:47:03.982
You didn't steal it, did you?

01:47:04.192 --> 01:47:07.110
Ha, ha. No, I didn't steal it.

01:47:07.278 --> 01:47:09.404
It's a present for you to keep.

01:47:09.572 --> 01:47:11.823
A Merry Christmas, Tiny Tim.

01:47:13.242 --> 01:47:15.493
You still don't recognize me,
do you, Bob Cratchit?

01:47:15.703 --> 01:47:17.829
Yes. Uh, no.

01:47:17.997 --> 01:47:20.415
- You're Father Christmas?
- No.

01:47:20.625 --> 01:47:21.666
[SHRIEKS]

01:47:21.834 --> 01:47:24.211
It's Mr. Scrooge. He's gone mad.

01:47:24.378 --> 01:47:26.963
It's all right, my dear.
There's nothing to be frightened of.

01:47:27.173 --> 01:47:28.506
No, I haven't gone mad.

01:47:28.674 --> 01:47:31.301
And on Monday
when your salary will be doubled...

01:47:31.469 --> 01:47:32.510
Doubled? He has gone mad.

01:47:32.678 --> 01:47:35.472
- We'll sit together and discuss
how I can help your family.

01:47:35.640 --> 01:47:39.893
To start with, we'll find the right
doctors to get Tiny Tim well.

01:47:40.061 --> 01:47:42.187
And we will get him well,
you know, Bob.

01:47:42.355 --> 01:47:45.023
Yes, I believe you.
I'll believe anything.

01:47:45.191 --> 01:47:49.778
And may this be the merriest
Christmas of all our lives.

01:47:49.987 --> 01:47:51.029
[CHEERING]

01:47:51.197 --> 01:47:53.114
Tom Jenkins, Tom Jenkins.

01:47:53.282 --> 01:47:55.033
About that 6 pounds you owe me.

01:47:55.201 --> 01:47:57.452
You agreed to give me
a few more days, I just need...

01:47:57.620 --> 01:48:01.289
You can keep it.
It's my Christmas present to you.

01:48:01.457 --> 01:48:04.793
God bless you this Christmas day,
Mr. Scrooge.

01:48:05.002 --> 01:48:06.836
Thank you very much.

01:48:07.004 --> 01:48:08.380
[SINGING]
Thank you very much

01:48:08.547 --> 01:48:12.676
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:48:12.885 --> 01:48:14.803
It sounds a bit bizarre

01:48:14.971 --> 01:48:20.392
But things the way they are
I feel as if another life's begun for me

01:48:22.561 --> 01:48:25.897
And that goes for anyone else
who owes me money, you can keep it.

01:48:26.065 --> 01:48:30.235
As of this day,
all my debts are ended.

01:48:30.861 --> 01:48:34.906
[ALL SINGING] And if I had a drum
I'd have to bang it

01:48:35.074 --> 01:48:39.661
To add a sort of
Humpty Dumpty touch

01:48:41.038 --> 01:48:44.499
But since I left my drummer at home
I'll simply have to say

01:48:44.667 --> 01:48:49.045
Thank you very, very, very much

01:48:49.213 --> 01:48:51.047
PUPPETS [SINGING]:
Thank you very much

01:48:51.215 --> 01:48:52.716
Thank you very much

01:48:52.925 --> 01:48:56.761
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:48:56.971 --> 01:48:58.805
It isn't every day

01:48:59.015 --> 01:49:00.807
Good fortune comes my way

01:49:01.017 --> 01:49:04.936
I never thought
The future would be fun for me

01:49:08.983 --> 01:49:12.861
And if I had a bugle I would blow it

01:49:13.029 --> 01:49:17.198
To add a sort of
How's your father touch

01:49:17.408 --> 01:49:21.119
But since I left my bugle at home
I'll simply have to say

01:49:21.287 --> 01:49:23.038
Gentlemen, Merry Christmas.

01:49:23.247 --> 01:49:25.206
ALL:
Merry Christmas, Mr. Scrooge.

01:49:25.416 --> 01:49:27.292
Come to my office
on Monday morning

01:49:27.460 --> 01:49:30.754
and I will give you a hundred guineas
for your most worthy cause.

01:49:30.963 --> 01:49:32.589
And the same every Christmas.

01:49:32.757 --> 01:49:35.216
Thank you very, very much,
Mr. Scrooge.

01:49:36.677 --> 01:49:41.973
[ALL SINGING]
Thank you very, very, very much

01:49:42.850 --> 01:49:46.686
Thank you very much

01:49:46.896 --> 01:49:50.690
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:49:50.858 --> 01:49:52.609
The future looks all right

01:49:52.777 --> 01:49:54.652
In fact it looks so bright

01:49:54.820 --> 01:49:59.157
I feel as if they're polishing
The sun for me

01:49:59.367 --> 01:50:04.287
- Sing a Christmas carol
- Sing a Christmas carol

01:50:04.497 --> 01:50:09.000
Sing a Christmas carol
Like the children do

01:50:09.210 --> 01:50:12.754
And if I had a cannon I would fire it

01:50:12.922 --> 01:50:17.008
To add a sort of celebration touch

01:50:17.385 --> 01:50:18.968
And enjoy the beauty

01:50:19.136 --> 01:50:22.347
All the joy and beauty
That a Merry Christmas...

01:50:22.556 --> 01:50:26.226
And since I left my cannon at home

01:50:26.435 --> 01:50:29.979
- I'll simply have to say
- Christmas is here

01:50:30.189 --> 01:50:37.904
Thank you very, very, very much

01:50:38.739 --> 01:50:41.783
Thank you very much

01:50:41.951 --> 01:50:46.121
That's the nicest thing
That anyone's ever done for me

01:50:46.288 --> 01:50:50.166
I may sound double Dutch
But my delight is such

01:50:50.334 --> 01:50:52.335
I feel as if a losing war

01:50:52.545 --> 01:50:54.212
- Has been won for me
- Come along, boys.

01:50:54.380 --> 01:50:58.133
And if I had a flag
I'd hang me flag out

01:50:58.342 --> 01:51:04.180
To add a sort of final victory touch

01:51:04.348 --> 01:51:07.725
But since I left me flag at home

01:51:08.436 --> 01:51:10.937
I'll simply have to say

